1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,800
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 8</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:44,971 --> 00:00:47,771
If I knew Ms. Jang was never
going to come back here,

3
00:00:48,099 --> 00:00:50,639
I should've at least said goodbye to her.

4
00:00:51,644 --> 00:00:54,984
It's good that she was able to leave
after she got rid

5
00:00:56,399 --> 00:00:57,859
of her old, deep grudges.

6
00:00:58,818 --> 00:01:01,608
Let's not forget to say goodbye
to each other before we leave.

7
00:01:01,696 --> 00:01:04,066
Don't leave without saying anything.
I'm serious.

8
00:01:04,574 --> 00:01:05,624
Promise me.

9
00:01:10,204 --> 00:01:11,214
You too.

10
00:01:16,168 --> 00:01:20,048
But what do you think is
going to happen to this hotel?

11
00:01:20,131 --> 00:01:23,091
As always, the Grim Reaper
didn't give us a straight answer.

12
00:01:23,217 --> 00:01:27,097
But it seems like Mago is getting ready
to welcome a new owner.

13
00:01:48,242 --> 00:01:51,122
I should let this sit to ferment
until the next full moon.

14
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,830
Now, I just need to add

15
00:01:54,916 --> 00:01:57,536
the most important ingredient,
the Moon Flower.

16
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:12,679
Oh, dear.

17
00:02:13,601 --> 00:02:15,811
We're out of Moon Flowers.

18
00:02:17,605 --> 00:02:19,435
<i>I heard you asked your sister
at the chemist's shop</i>

19
00:02:20,733 --> 00:02:22,323
to start making a new batch of wine

20
00:02:22,401 --> 00:02:24,571
for the new owner
of the Guest House of the Moon.

21
00:02:24,779 --> 00:02:27,619
The wine is currently being fermented.

22
00:02:27,782 --> 00:02:29,412
It will taste bitter and horrible

23
00:02:29,492 --> 00:02:31,832
to someone who holds a deep grudge.

24
00:02:32,453 --> 00:02:34,543
When Man-wol first drank that wine,

25
00:02:34,622 --> 00:02:37,502
she told me that she'd like
to pluck out my tongue.

26
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:41,500
<i>Whoever drinks that wine
will be influenced</i>

27
00:02:41,587 --> 00:02:43,007
<i>by the power of the moon</i>

28
00:02:43,089 --> 00:02:45,629
<i>and will no longer be
a part of life or death.</i>

29
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:50,143
<i>The Moon Tree will suck in
their remaining life</i>

30
00:02:50,221 --> 00:02:52,561
<i>and replace the body.</i>

31
00:02:52,848 --> 00:02:55,638
<i>And the person's soul will be tied
down to the Moon Tree</i>

32
00:02:55,726 --> 00:02:58,516
<i>and become the owner
of the Guest House of the Moon.</i>

33
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:05,243
The wine will be ready
by the next full moon.

34
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:09,069
But we're out of the most important
ingredient, the Moon Flower.

35
00:03:09,156 --> 00:03:10,696
I'll look for them.

36
00:03:11,742 --> 00:03:13,202
Where can I find them?

37
00:03:13,994 --> 00:03:18,464
They only bloom in the garden
of the Guest House of the Moon.

38
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,291
But there's not a single flower here.

39
00:03:21,585 --> 00:03:23,165
But I do recall seeing a flower bloom

40
00:03:23,462 --> 00:03:25,802
at the garden that existed 200 years ago.

41
00:03:25,881 --> 00:03:28,931
Then I should go to the Guest House
of the Moon that existed 200 years ago.

42
00:03:29,009 --> 00:03:30,549
You don't need to go.

43
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:35,020
I'll send someone else there.

44
00:03:53,242 --> 00:03:55,122
You came to work early again.

45
00:03:55,786 --> 00:03:56,866
I just wanted to check

46
00:03:57,663 --> 00:03:58,913
if she came back.

47
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:06,090
I have something for you, Mr. Koo.

48
00:04:14,221 --> 00:04:17,351
I heard this medicine will get rid
of your ability to see ghosts.

49
00:04:17,975 --> 00:04:19,015
Ms. Jang

50
00:04:19,643 --> 00:04:22,523
once asked me for a favor.

51
00:04:27,068 --> 00:04:28,818
If you think

52
00:04:29,945 --> 00:04:33,025
Chan-sung should no longer come here
anymore,

53
00:04:33,699 --> 00:04:35,079
I want you to give him this.

54
00:04:36,077 --> 00:04:37,827
Why are you giving that to me?

55
00:04:40,998 --> 00:04:42,878
I'm giving it to you just in case

56
00:04:44,543 --> 00:04:46,803
because I trust you the most.

57
00:04:48,964 --> 00:04:51,764
Up until now,
I trusted that she would come back.

58
00:04:52,635 --> 00:04:53,835
But now,

59
00:04:56,514 --> 00:04:57,814
I think...

60
00:05:00,976 --> 00:05:02,936
it's time to give you this.

61
00:05:11,445 --> 00:05:15,405
I guess you think
that she isn't going to return.

62
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:18,290
Ms. Jang has left this medicine for you

63
00:05:18,452 --> 00:05:21,122
because she wanted you
to start living in reality,

64
00:05:23,165 --> 00:05:26,835
instead of staying here
where she no longer exists.

65
00:05:49,775 --> 00:05:50,855
Chan-sung.

66
00:05:53,821 --> 00:05:55,031
Ta-da.

67
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:58,119
Guess what I'm about to go eat.

68
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:07,210
God, you have no clue at all.

69
00:06:07,376 --> 00:06:08,836
It's obviously rice with thistle.

70
00:06:08,919 --> 00:06:11,419
This is thistle,
the white part is rice, the sauce,

71
00:06:11,505 --> 00:06:12,665
and the spoon.

72
00:06:12,882 --> 00:06:13,922
Okay?

73
00:06:14,341 --> 00:06:15,261
Let's go.

74
00:06:15,342 --> 00:06:18,262
Oh, wait. My phone.
I have to take pictures.

75
00:06:34,945 --> 00:06:38,155
Why are you staring at me like that?
You're way too naughty.

76
00:06:48,292 --> 00:06:49,422
What is this?

77
00:06:49,585 --> 00:06:51,875
Did you bring
those special service requests again?

78
00:06:53,255 --> 00:06:55,415
Okay, fine. Bring those to me.

79
00:06:55,507 --> 00:06:56,757
Give me those.

80
00:06:56,842 --> 00:06:59,432
What will a ghost have to do
in the bedroom all night long?

81
00:06:59,511 --> 00:07:02,511
I can just work
and look into other people's dream calls.

82
00:07:03,349 --> 00:07:05,639
Harvard? What do they teach there?

83
00:07:05,726 --> 00:07:07,806
Do they only make you study?

84
00:07:08,103 --> 00:07:09,653
I don't even want to see you. Leave.

85
00:07:31,126 --> 00:07:34,876
Chan-sung, once you leave our hotel,

86
00:07:34,964 --> 00:07:38,184
you'll become an even greater person
than Hwang Mun-suk.

87
00:07:38,842 --> 00:07:43,062
You'll live long,
and you'll become very rich too.

88
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,810
This hotel guarantees it.

89
00:07:46,976 --> 00:07:50,766
But you can't show off like that already.

90
00:07:53,107 --> 00:07:54,187
Hey.

91
00:07:55,234 --> 00:07:56,444
What are you staring at?

92
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:52,960
Is Jang Man-wol here?

93
00:08:53,751 --> 00:08:56,171
I have to ask you to do something.

94
00:09:01,592 --> 00:09:02,892
What is it?

95
00:09:02,968 --> 00:09:06,598
You have to stop by Man-wol Inn.

96
00:09:07,222 --> 00:09:08,522
Man-wol Inn?

97
00:09:09,516 --> 00:09:12,306
Isn't that Del Luna's name
in the Joseon Dynasty?

98
00:09:12,394 --> 00:09:15,154
You're right. You need to go there for me.

99
00:09:18,108 --> 00:09:20,068
In the garden of Man-wol Inn,

100
00:09:20,152 --> 00:09:24,112
you'll find medicinal flowers
that shine under the moonlight.

101
00:09:24,239 --> 00:09:26,079
You can bring some of them to me.

102
00:09:26,158 --> 00:09:27,698
It's not a big deal.

103
00:09:28,452 --> 00:09:31,962
You can go there yourself.
Why are you asking me to do it?

104
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:34,420
Because I thought you might like it.

105
00:09:35,292 --> 00:09:36,632
If you go there,

106
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:40,340
you can get a good look
at the old Man-wol Inn.

107
00:09:41,799 --> 00:09:43,679
Then will I get to meet

108
00:09:45,052 --> 00:09:46,432
Jang Man-wol of that time?

109
00:09:47,388 --> 00:09:48,428
Probably.

110
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,730
If you don't want to do it,
then forget it.

111
00:09:52,309 --> 00:09:53,639
I'll do it.

112
00:09:59,566 --> 00:10:00,776
I'll go.

113
00:10:04,530 --> 00:10:06,620
<i>Once you go around the tree,</i>

114
00:10:06,698 --> 00:10:09,448
<i>you'll see the entrance to Man-wol Inn.</i>

115
00:10:09,535 --> 00:10:13,075
<i>You can return the opposite way.</i>

116
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:20,590
<i>Once you get there,
do not eat or drink anything.</i>

117
00:10:21,213 --> 00:10:24,803
<i>If you do, you won't be able to return.</i>

118
00:11:31,283 --> 00:11:34,543
MAN-WOL INN

119
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:50,143
You're the one
who ratted on me, aren't you?

120
00:11:50,219 --> 00:11:52,099
I just told the truth. What now?

121
00:11:52,179 --> 00:11:54,469
You couldn't just die alone, huh?

122
00:11:54,556 --> 00:11:57,346
-No, I couldn't!
-Kill me again, and see what happens!

123
00:11:57,434 --> 00:11:58,894
-Do you really want to die?
-Yes! Kill me!

124
00:11:58,977 --> 00:12:00,727
-That's Ms. Choe.
-Darn you!

125
00:12:00,812 --> 00:12:02,772
-You little...
-Please don't do this.

126
00:12:02,856 --> 00:12:06,356
Please calm down and come this way.

127
00:12:07,069 --> 00:12:08,779
My goodness.

128
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:18,792
Excuse me, is this the liquor
for Madam Jang?

129
00:12:18,872 --> 00:12:20,172
Yes.

130
00:12:24,169 --> 00:12:26,799
I cannot believe how much she's drinking.

131
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,220
That's Mr. Kim.

132
00:12:51,989 --> 00:12:53,239
Who goes there?

133
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:08,169
You are alive. How did you get in here?

134
00:13:10,841 --> 00:13:12,341
Are you here to steal?

135
00:13:16,054 --> 00:13:17,854
You are dressed oddly.

136
00:13:18,724 --> 00:13:19,984
Where are you from?

137
00:13:21,435 --> 00:13:22,685
Jang Man-wol...

138
00:13:25,063 --> 00:13:26,863
How do you know my name?

139
00:13:28,775 --> 00:13:30,105
Are you...

140
00:13:36,658 --> 00:13:39,408
Oh from Dangyong sent you here, right?

141
00:13:39,786 --> 00:13:42,616
You probably came here
after you saw the IOU I gave him.

142
00:13:43,623 --> 00:13:46,673
Go and tell Oh Chung-hwan

143
00:13:46,752 --> 00:13:49,672
that I will be there myself
in a month to pay him back.

144
00:13:59,014 --> 00:14:01,684
I came from a place
much further than that.

145
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:04,390
You cannot

146
00:14:05,395 --> 00:14:06,975
recognize me at this moment.

147
00:14:09,858 --> 00:14:10,938
You can

148
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:13,610
see ghosts.

149
00:14:15,405 --> 00:14:17,615
Who gave you that ability?

150
00:14:23,163 --> 00:14:25,673
Man-wol!

151
00:14:25,749 --> 00:14:29,209
-Darn it.
-I came back for you!

152
00:14:29,294 --> 00:14:31,094
-You came again.
-I didn't even die

153
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:32,961
-and came back.
-Madam Jang isn't here.

154
00:14:33,048 --> 00:14:34,508
-What's wrong?
-I came yesterday,

155
00:14:34,591 --> 00:14:37,971
I'm here today,
and I'll come tomorrow too.

156
00:14:38,053 --> 00:14:40,223
Damn it, that lousy old hag.

157
00:14:40,514 --> 00:14:42,314
She's here again.

158
00:14:42,391 --> 00:14:44,641
Man-wol, I'm here again.

159
00:14:44,726 --> 00:14:46,646
Isn't that Mago?

160
00:14:46,853 --> 00:14:47,733
Bring some rice!

161
00:14:47,813 --> 00:14:49,733
-You know her?
-We don't have any.

162
00:14:49,815 --> 00:14:50,765
Yes.

163
00:14:51,942 --> 00:14:53,902
I've met her five other sisters so far.

164
00:14:54,403 --> 00:14:55,703
But I haven't met her.

165
00:14:58,156 --> 00:15:00,076
Are you close to Mago?

166
00:15:01,535 --> 00:15:03,905
Her sisters treated me nicely.

167
00:15:03,995 --> 00:15:05,245
Is that so?

168
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,543
Do you want a drink?

169
00:15:20,721 --> 00:15:23,471
You've probably just started working here.

170
00:15:23,724 --> 00:15:26,774
Yes, it's been less than two years.

171
00:15:28,812 --> 00:15:30,362
This drink is from this world.

172
00:15:30,605 --> 00:15:32,895
It's been a while
since we had a living guest.

173
00:15:34,317 --> 00:15:36,067
Don't you have a human manager?

174
00:15:36,153 --> 00:15:37,153
"A manager"?

175
00:15:37,988 --> 00:15:39,948
You must mean a human steward.

176
00:15:40,323 --> 00:15:43,033
He died a short while ago
so we don't have any at the moment.

177
00:15:43,452 --> 00:15:47,212
Are you the new steward
brought in by Mago?

178
00:15:48,749 --> 00:15:49,669
No, I'm not.

179
00:15:51,668 --> 00:15:54,708
She mistook me
for someone Oh from Dangyong sent.

180
00:15:54,796 --> 00:15:55,916
Who is that?

181
00:15:56,006 --> 00:15:59,046
Dangyong is the gambling den,
and Oh is the money lender.

182
00:15:59,134 --> 00:16:00,724
Gambling den...

183
00:16:01,511 --> 00:16:03,221
Does Jang Man-wol gamble?

184
00:16:05,599 --> 00:16:08,849
<i>After the death of the human steward
who took care of her for a long time,</i>

185
00:16:08,935 --> 00:16:12,355
<i>we thought she went out at nights
because she was feeling empty.</i>

186
00:16:13,690 --> 00:16:16,320
<i>But it turned out that she was gambling.</i>

187
00:16:21,865 --> 00:16:23,405
What should I do?

188
00:16:26,995 --> 00:16:28,205
I'm all in.

189
00:16:29,623 --> 00:16:31,543
If you are scared, just croak.

190
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:34,093
-I'm all in.
-Here's my house deed.

191
00:16:37,047 --> 00:16:38,667
Okay, show me.

192
00:16:43,345 --> 00:16:45,925
This is good enough.

193
00:16:46,014 --> 00:16:47,354
Wait!

194
00:16:48,058 --> 00:16:50,848
I'm sorry about this.

195
00:16:50,936 --> 00:16:54,726
How much is all this?

196
00:16:54,981 --> 00:16:56,731
<i>She worked with a ghost gambler.</i>

197
00:16:56,817 --> 00:16:58,817
<i>So she raked in all the money at first.</i>

198
00:16:59,110 --> 00:17:01,320
<i>Then Mago found out about it.</i>

199
00:17:01,905 --> 00:17:04,735
After that,
the Mago who brings in poverty,

200
00:17:04,825 --> 00:17:06,365
comes here every day.

201
00:17:06,451 --> 00:17:10,121
So Man-wol's storeroom is about
to be completely empty.

202
00:17:10,205 --> 00:17:12,285
She is gambling with the help
of a ghost gambler.

203
00:17:14,209 --> 00:17:15,959
The situation here is worse.

204
00:17:16,044 --> 00:17:18,804
We might have to sell
the farmland and this house.

205
00:17:19,422 --> 00:17:22,882
We need a proper human steward.

206
00:17:58,253 --> 00:17:59,503
Please enjoy yourselves.

207
00:18:13,643 --> 00:18:14,903
Jang Man-wol.

208
00:18:15,687 --> 00:18:17,227
Do you gamble?

209
00:18:19,691 --> 00:18:22,441
I was bored,
so I only played it as a game.

210
00:18:22,527 --> 00:18:23,607
A game?

211
00:18:24,029 --> 00:18:27,239
If you lived in my world,
you would have gone to prison.

212
00:18:27,324 --> 00:18:29,204
I am planning to stop.

213
00:18:29,284 --> 00:18:31,664
After I get back all the money I lost.

214
00:18:31,745 --> 00:18:34,205
If you think like that,
you will never be able to stop.

215
00:18:34,289 --> 00:18:36,709
I have to get back the money
to take care of the guests.

216
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,631
You don't need money
to take care of your guests.

217
00:18:39,628 --> 00:18:42,958
Is there anything you don't know?

218
00:18:46,468 --> 00:18:47,298
All right.

219
00:18:47,385 --> 00:18:50,595
It seems you have some relationship
with the Mago sisters.

220
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,390
Go and tell that old beggar woman you saw

221
00:18:53,725 --> 00:18:54,935
to leave this place.

222
00:18:55,101 --> 00:18:57,101
You can't drive deities out
just like that.

223
00:18:59,356 --> 00:19:00,356
That's right.

224
00:19:01,608 --> 00:19:04,948
That's why I can't just kick
that beggar out.

225
00:19:05,028 --> 00:19:06,108
Neither can I refuse her.

226
00:19:06,196 --> 00:19:08,446
She comes here every day
wanting me to gamble with her.

227
00:19:08,531 --> 00:19:09,951
I'll never win.

228
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:12,413
I'll become a beggar myself at this rate.

229
00:19:15,121 --> 00:19:18,211
I once persuaded a deity to leave a place.

230
00:19:19,167 --> 00:19:20,127
Really?

231
00:19:20,251 --> 00:19:21,801
If I persuade her,

232
00:19:22,295 --> 00:19:24,005
will you never gamble again?

233
00:19:24,923 --> 00:19:26,013
Never.

234
00:19:26,883 --> 00:19:28,893
I will put my hand on the line.

235
00:19:44,859 --> 00:19:45,939
Oh, gosh.

236
00:19:47,070 --> 00:19:48,360
It tastes

237
00:19:49,531 --> 00:19:50,781
horrible.

238
00:19:53,243 --> 00:19:54,333
Did you

239
00:19:55,787 --> 00:19:57,037
enjoy your meal?

240
00:19:57,664 --> 00:19:58,874
Who are you?

241
00:19:58,957 --> 00:20:00,207
I am here for the Moon Flower.

242
00:20:00,291 --> 00:20:02,961
My name is Koo Chan-sung.
Your sister sent me.

243
00:20:03,628 --> 00:20:05,128
My big sister sent you?

244
00:20:05,213 --> 00:20:08,633
You came from a very faraway place.

245
00:20:08,717 --> 00:20:11,297
I know you are punishing Jang Man-wol
for what she did.

246
00:20:11,386 --> 00:20:14,926
But can't you please stop now?

247
00:20:16,391 --> 00:20:18,391
I plan to make her go broke.

248
00:20:18,476 --> 00:20:19,886
Please go easy on her.

249
00:20:20,228 --> 00:20:22,978
I don't like to see her suffer too much.

250
00:20:23,398 --> 00:20:24,768
Why not?

251
00:20:27,277 --> 00:20:28,817
If you don't like it,

252
00:20:30,071 --> 00:20:32,201
will you play a round

253
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,373
with me?

254
00:20:35,535 --> 00:20:37,995
You can choose the game.

255
00:20:39,748 --> 00:20:42,668
How about a game of Go?

256
00:20:43,084 --> 00:20:44,254
A game of Go?

257
00:20:45,670 --> 00:20:47,010
I like that.

258
00:21:05,231 --> 00:21:08,071
What's going on? Is he winning?

259
00:21:08,234 --> 00:21:10,904
It's a very close game.

260
00:21:10,987 --> 00:21:13,067
This young man is doing quite well
against a deity.

261
00:21:13,156 --> 00:21:15,526
He was so sure of himself.

262
00:21:15,617 --> 00:21:18,827
He said something about Harvard.
Do you know Harvard?

263
00:21:19,204 --> 00:21:20,464
He studied there.

264
00:21:20,538 --> 00:21:23,168
He said he had a great brain,
if nothing else.

265
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:25,206
I guess he wasn't lying.

266
00:21:25,335 --> 00:21:26,955
You are so noisy.

267
00:21:47,607 --> 00:21:48,897
Oh, no.

268
00:21:57,575 --> 00:21:58,615
I lost.

269
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:03,250
Go away right now.

270
00:22:03,331 --> 00:22:04,751
Don't ever come back.

271
00:22:06,918 --> 00:22:08,708
-I'm going.
-Quickly.

272
00:22:11,756 --> 00:22:13,506
Well done.

273
00:22:20,765 --> 00:22:22,805
I WILL NEVER ENTER A GAMBLING DEN AGAIN

274
00:22:22,892 --> 00:22:24,852
Are you happy now?

275
00:22:25,353 --> 00:22:26,603
Please sign it.

276
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:30,150
Write your name.

277
00:22:32,402 --> 00:22:34,072
How fastidious.

278
00:22:36,155 --> 00:22:39,195
I noticed you had too many horses
in the stable.

279
00:22:39,284 --> 00:22:41,704
Keep only three, and sell the rest
to pay off your debt.

280
00:22:41,786 --> 00:22:42,746
Just three?

281
00:22:42,829 --> 00:22:44,869
You'll say you want
to make the stable look good.

282
00:22:44,956 --> 00:22:47,126
But that's not acceptable.
Pay off your debt first.

283
00:22:49,460 --> 00:22:51,170
Or I'll call the old beggar again.

284
00:22:51,254 --> 00:22:54,594
All right. I will sell them. Okay?

285
00:22:56,342 --> 00:22:59,052
JANG MAN-WOL

286
00:22:59,137 --> 00:23:02,097
There. We're done with this, right?

287
00:23:05,351 --> 00:23:08,351
Don't go to gambling dens if you're bored.

288
00:23:08,438 --> 00:23:09,768
Find a new hobby.

289
00:23:16,321 --> 00:23:17,411
Look.

290
00:23:25,121 --> 00:23:27,921
Joseon is shaped like a tiger.

291
00:23:28,791 --> 00:23:29,791
A tiger?

292
00:23:31,711 --> 00:23:34,131
Bibimbap is delicious in Jeonju.

293
00:23:34,213 --> 00:23:36,343
And in winter, here.

294
00:23:36,466 --> 00:23:38,756
Pohang is famous for half-dried herrings.

295
00:23:39,260 --> 00:23:42,350
You will love
the Pyongyang <i>naengmyeon </i>up there.

296
00:23:43,848 --> 00:23:46,178
Are you telling me
to go on a gourmet tour?

297
00:23:46,351 --> 00:23:47,771
Have you eaten all of them?

298
00:23:47,852 --> 00:23:49,352
Yes, I have.

299
00:23:49,896 --> 00:23:51,226
With someone.

300
00:23:57,570 --> 00:24:00,530
Will it be more fun than gambling?

301
00:24:00,615 --> 00:24:01,815
You will like it

302
00:24:03,785 --> 00:24:06,405
so much that you'll enjoy it
for the next 200 years.

303
00:24:07,914 --> 00:24:09,334
Do you want to go with me?

304
00:24:14,963 --> 00:24:15,963
Hey.

305
00:24:17,090 --> 00:24:19,340
Would you be interested in working
as a steward here?

306
00:24:20,385 --> 00:24:22,215
I like you.

307
00:24:39,570 --> 00:24:42,570
Stay by my side here.

308
00:24:48,913 --> 00:24:50,623
<i>Once you get there,</i>

309
00:24:50,707 --> 00:24:53,377
<i>do not eat or drink anything.</i>

310
00:24:54,585 --> 00:24:57,915
<i>If you do, you won't be able to return.</i>

311
00:25:02,301 --> 00:25:04,851
If I stay here with you,
I won't have to worry

312
00:25:07,432 --> 00:25:08,982
about you vanishing.

313
00:25:10,226 --> 00:25:11,596
There.

314
00:25:12,562 --> 00:25:14,772
Drink up, Chan-sung.

315
00:25:38,379 --> 00:25:39,879
I have to go back.

316
00:25:41,299 --> 00:25:43,339
There's a woman I must wait for.

317
00:25:46,679 --> 00:25:47,889
Is she your lover?

318
00:25:50,099 --> 00:25:51,099
Yes.

319
00:25:52,810 --> 00:25:54,690
She's someone I love so much.

320
00:25:58,816 --> 00:26:00,026
It's too bad.

321
00:26:06,616 --> 00:26:09,036
I guess I might regret it once I go back.

322
00:26:36,854 --> 00:26:38,314
If you leave,

323
00:26:38,731 --> 00:26:41,441
their memories about you,
who traveled back in time,

324
00:26:41,526 --> 00:26:43,276
will disappear.

325
00:26:43,361 --> 00:26:46,821
Did you come to check up on me
because you were worried I wouldn't leave?

326
00:26:46,906 --> 00:26:50,196
It's your choice whether you go back

327
00:26:50,284 --> 00:26:51,744
or stay.

328
00:26:53,412 --> 00:26:55,832
If you stay here, you'll probably become

329
00:26:55,998 --> 00:27:02,588
Man-wol's 85th human steward
before you die.

330
00:27:04,674 --> 00:27:07,304
Will you go back to being someone
who'll send her off,

331
00:27:07,385 --> 00:27:09,845
or will you remain here
as someone passing by?

332
00:27:10,304 --> 00:27:11,224
That's

333
00:27:12,056 --> 00:27:13,596
for you to decide.

334
00:29:25,356 --> 00:29:28,776
Thank you for bringing these for me.

335
00:29:29,735 --> 00:29:32,025
I can see why you sent me there.

336
00:29:32,446 --> 00:29:35,196
You helped me realize how I should feel

337
00:29:36,701 --> 00:29:38,121
while waiting for her.

338
00:29:38,828 --> 00:29:40,158
For now,

339
00:29:41,455 --> 00:29:42,825
you should be happy.

340
00:29:43,958 --> 00:29:45,708
Man-wol has come back.

341
00:30:23,205 --> 00:30:24,415
She must be here.

342
00:30:41,098 --> 00:30:42,478
I'm sorry I'm late.

343
00:30:43,726 --> 00:30:45,686
It was a short period of time there,

344
00:30:46,854 --> 00:30:48,564
but you must've waited for a long time.

345
00:30:49,940 --> 00:30:50,820
Ms. Jang!

346
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:52,570
-Ms. Jang!
-Ms. Jang.

347
00:30:52,652 --> 00:30:54,032
Ms. Jang!

348
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,410
Ms. Jang.

349
00:31:05,081 --> 00:31:06,171
Ms. Jang.

350
00:31:26,602 --> 00:31:28,812
I'm glad Ms. Jang is back.

351
00:31:29,188 --> 00:31:32,648
I was upset since we started
talking about a new owner.

352
00:31:32,733 --> 00:31:33,863
Ms. Jang must've taken a while

353
00:31:33,943 --> 00:31:36,653
because she had to see him off
on the bridge to the afterlife.

354
00:31:37,530 --> 00:31:40,160
But because she stepped on the bridge,

355
00:31:40,491 --> 00:31:43,121
Ms. Jang has lost a lot of her memories.

356
00:31:46,414 --> 00:31:50,084
Her memories of the person
she sent off is almost gone.

357
00:31:50,501 --> 00:31:53,211
Do older memories disappear first?

358
00:31:53,462 --> 00:31:56,342
The memories that have bothered us
for the longest time

359
00:31:56,841 --> 00:31:58,721
will disappear first.

360
00:31:59,969 --> 00:32:04,009
It seems so futile,
but it gives me a sense of relief.

361
00:32:06,809 --> 00:32:08,189
Don't worry.

362
00:32:08,561 --> 00:32:11,271
I didn't forget anything about you.

363
00:32:14,608 --> 00:32:17,818
Is that so? Then should I test you?

364
00:32:18,946 --> 00:32:20,276
You're so fastidious.

365
00:32:21,532 --> 00:32:23,452
The red car or me?

366
00:32:24,243 --> 00:32:25,833
You. Happy?

367
00:32:26,662 --> 00:32:28,332
Okay, that's the most important thing.

368
00:32:29,165 --> 00:32:30,745
Do you remember
how many cars you have left?

369
00:32:30,833 --> 00:32:31,923
Three...

370
00:32:33,169 --> 00:32:36,049
Hey! You didn't sell them off
while I was away, did you?

371
00:32:36,297 --> 00:32:37,627
I didn't sell your cars,

372
00:32:39,175 --> 00:32:40,715
although I asked the horse to be sold off.

373
00:32:42,094 --> 00:32:44,434
Do you remember Oh from Dangyong?

374
00:32:47,767 --> 00:32:49,637
How do you know Oh Chung-hwan?

375
00:32:50,895 --> 00:32:52,975
Even your memories
from 200 years ago are safe.

376
00:32:53,189 --> 00:32:54,359
That's good.

377
00:32:55,232 --> 00:32:56,902
Did Mr. Kim tell you?

378
00:32:57,026 --> 00:32:58,486
I'm sure he did.

379
00:32:58,569 --> 00:33:00,319
You guys must have talked behind my back.

380
00:33:00,404 --> 00:33:01,614
What else did he say?

381
00:33:01,906 --> 00:33:03,026
Have a drink.

382
00:33:03,657 --> 00:33:06,037
I refused a drink from a woman
just a while ago.

383
00:33:06,118 --> 00:33:07,328
So I need this now.

384
00:33:08,871 --> 00:33:11,291
"A woman"? Why are you lying?

385
00:33:11,582 --> 00:33:13,582
There's no way
you would have another woman.

386
00:33:14,168 --> 00:33:16,588
Are you upset because I made you wait?

387
00:33:16,670 --> 00:33:19,170
But I do. She's someone really beautiful.

388
00:33:20,883 --> 00:33:24,183
Chan-sung, don't underestimate me.

389
00:33:24,470 --> 00:33:27,100
I don't get jealous at all.

390
00:33:27,181 --> 00:33:30,021
I'd just kill you. Die.

391
00:33:30,643 --> 00:33:32,193
I see your hands are intact.

392
00:33:32,269 --> 00:33:33,809
It looks like you kept your promise.

393
00:33:36,732 --> 00:33:38,862
I went to Man-wol Inn to meet Madam Jang.

394
00:33:39,401 --> 00:33:41,451
-Me?
-Mago sent me there.

395
00:33:41,821 --> 00:33:43,701
And I was the one who saved you

396
00:33:43,781 --> 00:33:45,911
from losing everything on gambling.

397
00:33:47,284 --> 00:33:48,624
I don't have such a memory.

398
00:33:48,702 --> 00:33:50,412
I was told that you wouldn't remember.

399
00:33:51,288 --> 00:33:55,288
I only went there briefly
to find the Moon Flowers.

400
00:33:57,753 --> 00:33:59,303
"Moon Flowers"?

401
00:34:00,714 --> 00:34:01,974
Did she need them?

402
00:34:02,591 --> 00:34:04,261
She told me she was making some wine.

403
00:34:04,969 --> 00:34:06,969
-Do you know about it?
-Yes.

404
00:34:07,888 --> 00:34:10,978
I had a taste of it a long time ago.

405
00:34:11,433 --> 00:34:13,273
It was disgusting.

406
00:34:17,189 --> 00:34:20,989
I guess Mago is making the wine again.

407
00:35:08,282 --> 00:35:10,992
<i>But her brother, Ji Hyeon-jung,</i>

408
00:35:11,702 --> 00:35:13,452
died many years ago.

409
00:35:33,682 --> 00:35:34,852
Hyeon-jung!

410
00:35:35,643 --> 00:35:36,773
Tae-seok!

411
00:35:37,353 --> 00:35:38,693
Hey, give me a ride.

412
00:35:38,854 --> 00:35:39,814
Where's your bike?

413
00:35:39,939 --> 00:35:41,069
I left it at home.

414
00:35:41,148 --> 00:35:42,568
-Hop on.
-Nice.

415
00:35:43,108 --> 00:35:43,978
Just kidding.

416
00:35:44,068 --> 00:35:45,068
My gosh.

417
00:35:48,739 --> 00:35:51,699
<i>So, the old man was
your friend from school.</i>

418
00:35:52,368 --> 00:35:55,078
<i>Then I guess he's not a bad person
who stole your life.</i>

419
00:35:55,871 --> 00:35:59,001
He's a good friend who's been taking care
of your sister for you.

420
00:36:01,794 --> 00:36:05,674
I did some research on Dr. Ji Hyeon-jung.

421
00:36:06,674 --> 00:36:07,684
Look.

422
00:36:08,217 --> 00:36:10,507
He did a lot of good deeds as a doctor.

423
00:36:11,303 --> 00:36:13,353
And it seems
that a lot of people respect him.

424
00:36:13,681 --> 00:36:15,981
He lived a really good life
with your name.

425
00:36:16,892 --> 00:36:19,482
Yes, he lived a very diligent life.

426
00:36:20,187 --> 00:36:22,897
He's taking care of your sister
at the hospital he founded,

427
00:36:22,982 --> 00:36:24,442
so wouldn't your sister

428
00:36:24,775 --> 00:36:27,355
be able to live
for at least ten more years?

429
00:36:32,616 --> 00:36:35,286
Hey, I got a text
from your sister's caregiver.

430
00:36:35,869 --> 00:36:36,909
What?

431
00:36:37,329 --> 00:36:39,669
I got her number that day.

432
00:36:49,633 --> 00:36:50,883
Hyeon-jung.

433
00:37:14,491 --> 00:37:16,791
Fortunately, she's stable again.

434
00:37:16,869 --> 00:37:20,119
Like always, she managed
to overcome the worst.

435
00:37:20,205 --> 00:37:22,365
Thank you for everything.

436
00:37:22,583 --> 00:37:23,673
Bye, then.

437
00:37:30,299 --> 00:37:32,179
Hyeon-mi's okay again.

438
00:37:36,513 --> 00:37:38,723
You must be very disappointed.

439
00:37:55,908 --> 00:37:56,948
Young lady.

440
00:38:03,499 --> 00:38:05,959
Did you take my photo?

441
00:38:06,335 --> 00:38:08,085
What photo?

442
00:38:08,170 --> 00:38:11,630
You once talked to me
about Hyeon-jung last time.

443
00:38:11,715 --> 00:38:14,465
You took the photo of me
and Hyeon-jung, didn't you?

444
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:16,930
You have a photo of Hyeon-jung?

445
00:38:18,305 --> 00:38:20,265
I guess you really were friends.

446
00:38:22,226 --> 00:38:26,056
You're his friend, so make sure
his sister stays alive for a long time.

447
00:38:27,523 --> 00:38:29,823
Hyeon-jung's always watching you.

448
00:38:30,567 --> 00:38:31,777
He was also watching you

449
00:38:32,736 --> 00:38:34,066
just a while ago.

450
00:38:40,619 --> 00:38:43,749
Wait. Is Hyeon-jung alive?

451
00:38:44,373 --> 00:38:47,583
Did he leave his sister with me
and make me live like this

452
00:38:47,668 --> 00:38:49,418
when he's still alive?

453
00:38:50,087 --> 00:38:53,297
Where is Hyeon-jung? Where's he now?

454
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:59,720
My goodness, you really used to be
an elite student, Hyeon-jung.

455
00:38:59,805 --> 00:39:01,635
I was also really popular.

456
00:39:01,723 --> 00:39:03,983
I can imagine.
Even the ghosts here told me

457
00:39:04,059 --> 00:39:06,269
their hearts fluttered
every time you smiled at them.

458
00:39:06,353 --> 00:39:08,063
I'm sure you were popular.

459
00:39:08,939 --> 00:39:11,729
Back when I passed
the National State Exam at a young age

460
00:39:11,817 --> 00:39:13,187
and was known as a genius,

461
00:39:13,485 --> 00:39:15,645
all the young ladies in the neighborhood

462
00:39:15,737 --> 00:39:19,487
gathered around my house
so they could hear me read out loud.

463
00:39:19,575 --> 00:39:21,735
I guess it was because
they could hear your voice

464
00:39:21,827 --> 00:39:23,497
but couldn't see your face.

465
00:39:23,954 --> 00:39:26,214
You do have a nice voice, Mr. Kim.

466
00:39:26,290 --> 00:39:29,920
A man should have a nice voice.
Don't you agree, Mr. Koo?

467
00:39:30,544 --> 00:39:33,214
But he has good looks
as well as a nice voice.

468
00:39:36,425 --> 00:39:38,965
The person next to you
must be your school friend.

469
00:39:39,428 --> 00:39:43,308
Yes, he's the person
who's taking care of my sister Hyeon-mi

470
00:39:43,807 --> 00:39:44,767
right now.

471
00:39:50,272 --> 00:39:54,692
And thanks to him,
Hyeon-mi was able to stay alive today.

472
00:39:59,114 --> 00:40:01,744
It seems like
Hyeon-jung will be leaving soon.

473
00:40:01,825 --> 00:40:03,485
So I've been thinking...

474
00:40:03,577 --> 00:40:06,617
How about we hold a special event for him
before he leaves

475
00:40:06,705 --> 00:40:08,825
with his sister once she comes here?

476
00:40:08,916 --> 00:40:12,456
Hyeon-jung never got to spend
much time with his sister.

477
00:40:12,544 --> 00:40:14,384
So how about we open up an amusement park

478
00:40:14,463 --> 00:40:17,013
so they could have fun together
even for a little while?

479
00:40:17,591 --> 00:40:19,221
An amusement park?

480
00:40:19,968 --> 00:40:23,558
And I don't mind
turning the bar into a kid-friendly cafe.

481
00:40:24,223 --> 00:40:27,143
He's been kindly waiting
for his sister for 70 years.

482
00:40:27,226 --> 00:40:30,056
He should at least get to talk
to his sister for a short while.

483
00:40:32,147 --> 00:40:35,437
Do you really think
his sister is the only reason

484
00:40:35,609 --> 00:40:37,529
he's been staying here?

485
00:40:38,528 --> 00:40:41,198
He may be a pure and kind young man,

486
00:40:41,281 --> 00:40:43,531
but do you really think
he's been waiting here

487
00:40:43,617 --> 00:40:46,867
for 70 years just because he was
worried about his sister?

488
00:40:51,124 --> 00:40:52,424
Have you all forgotten?

489
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:55,960
He came here after he got shot.

490
00:41:09,726 --> 00:41:12,436
If you didn't want to come
to the event for them,

491
00:41:12,521 --> 00:41:15,321
you could've just stayed quiet
instead of ruining the mood.

492
00:41:15,399 --> 00:41:16,779
I once

493
00:41:17,401 --> 00:41:20,531
shot someone with this gun.

494
00:41:21,571 --> 00:41:25,871
<i>I shot the ghost's enemy
with a bullet filled with her grudges...</i>

495
00:41:28,745 --> 00:41:30,655
<i>so that he could live in agony forever.</i>

496
00:41:32,249 --> 00:41:34,919
Are you saying you're going to do the same

497
00:41:35,002 --> 00:41:36,552
to the guy who killed Hyeon-jung?

498
00:41:38,130 --> 00:41:40,970
Hyeon-jung already shot his enemy

499
00:41:41,049 --> 00:41:43,509
with a bullet filled with his own grudges.

500
00:41:44,553 --> 00:41:46,183
What do you think that bullet is?

501
00:41:49,141 --> 00:41:52,771
It's Hyeon-mi.
I'm talking about his sister, Ji Hyeon-mi.

502
00:41:56,273 --> 00:42:00,323
<i>His little sister is almost blind
and mentally ill.</i>

503
00:42:01,028 --> 00:42:05,368
<i>And he kept her beside his enemy
and made him suffer forever.</i>

504
00:42:06,867 --> 00:42:10,037
It's true that Hyeon-jung has been
waiting here for 70 years

505
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,250
for his sister to come.

506
00:42:11,330 --> 00:42:15,380
But it's also true that he's used her
to harass the guy who killed him

507
00:42:15,459 --> 00:42:17,209
for 70 whole years.

508
00:42:17,711 --> 00:42:19,501
The person who killed Hyeon-jung

509
00:42:20,797 --> 00:42:23,007
is his friend
that's taking care of his sister?

510
00:42:34,311 --> 00:42:35,351
Yu-na.

511
00:42:35,687 --> 00:42:36,897
Hyeon-jung.

512
00:42:37,314 --> 00:42:41,194
I brought someone
who really wished to meet you.

513
00:42:41,943 --> 00:42:42,943
Me?

514
00:42:55,290 --> 00:42:56,380
Hyeon-jung.

515
00:43:07,594 --> 00:43:11,644
Ms. Jang, Hyeon-jung's so-called friend
just came.

516
00:43:12,182 --> 00:43:13,682
Yu-na brought him here.

517
00:43:15,268 --> 00:43:18,058
I guess he's here to ask him
for forgiveness.

518
00:43:27,739 --> 00:43:30,529
Hyeon-jung ran away
as soon as he saw the old man.

519
00:43:31,660 --> 00:43:33,120
I guess he doesn't want to meet him.

520
00:43:33,203 --> 00:43:35,623
I didn't bring him here for him.

521
00:43:35,956 --> 00:43:40,036
Hyeon-jung can get his stolen life back,
even if only a little,

522
00:43:41,837 --> 00:43:44,707
only while he's still alive.

523
00:43:44,923 --> 00:43:46,683
That's why I brought him here.

524
00:43:49,553 --> 00:43:51,603
Hyeon-jung needs to decide for himself.

525
00:44:11,825 --> 00:44:15,445
During the war,
a bombing killed both his parents.

526
00:44:15,537 --> 00:44:18,867
And Hyeon-jung barely managed
to save his little sister.

527
00:44:33,430 --> 00:44:34,850
Eat slowly.

528
00:44:37,184 --> 00:44:38,194
Is it good?

529
00:44:39,394 --> 00:44:42,734
Hyeon-mi, once we get
to our uncle's place in Busan,

530
00:44:42,814 --> 00:44:44,324
you can eat a lot of good food

531
00:44:44,399 --> 00:44:46,939
and get treated
so that you aren't in pain anymore.

532
00:44:48,111 --> 00:44:50,161
<i>His sister was badly hurt,</i>

533
00:44:50,238 --> 00:44:51,908
<i>so he was in a rush.</i>

534
00:44:51,990 --> 00:44:53,950
<i>Instead of going with the refugees,</i>

535
00:44:54,034 --> 00:44:56,794
<i>he decided to take shortcuts
through the mountains.</i>

536
00:45:16,389 --> 00:45:17,519
Do not move.

537
00:45:33,406 --> 00:45:34,566
Hyeon-jung?

538
00:45:35,992 --> 00:45:37,122
Tae-seok.

539
00:45:37,953 --> 00:45:40,253
<i>That's where he met a runaway soldier,</i>

540
00:45:40,789 --> 00:45:42,419
<i>who turned out to be his friend.</i>

541
00:45:49,422 --> 00:45:50,592
Eat slowly.

542
00:45:53,176 --> 00:45:55,006
My sister is badly hurt.

543
00:45:56,179 --> 00:45:57,759
Do you know the shortcut?

544
00:46:01,142 --> 00:46:04,272
We're headed to our uncle's place
in Busan.

545
00:46:04,980 --> 00:46:06,560
Come with us, Tae-seok.

546
00:46:12,821 --> 00:46:13,781
Take off your uniform.

547
00:46:15,323 --> 00:46:16,623
Take it off!

548
00:46:17,659 --> 00:46:20,119
I'll get shot and die if I'm wearing this,

549
00:46:21,454 --> 00:46:22,664
so take that off.

550
00:46:25,667 --> 00:46:26,877
Tae-seok.

551
00:46:36,636 --> 00:46:39,216
You can't take this.
Hyeon-mi's medicine is in here,

552
00:46:39,306 --> 00:46:40,806
and she'll die without it.

553
00:46:48,815 --> 00:46:50,475
Let it go before I shoot you.

554
00:47:20,013 --> 00:47:21,393
Hyeon-jung.

555
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:23,980
Hyeon-jung!

556
00:47:24,559 --> 00:47:25,939
Hyeon-jung!

557
00:47:26,770 --> 00:47:28,520
-Hyeon-jung!
-Hyeon-jung.

558
00:47:29,689 --> 00:47:32,029
I didn't do this on purpose.
You know that, right?

559
00:47:32,108 --> 00:47:33,818
-Hyeon-jung!
-Damn it.

560
00:47:33,985 --> 00:47:35,985
-Hyeon-jung!
-I'm sorry.

561
00:47:37,489 --> 00:47:39,029
JI HYEON-JUNG

562
00:47:39,699 --> 00:47:42,699
-Hyeon-jung!
-Take my sister with you.

563
00:47:43,036 --> 00:47:44,326
Hyeon-jung!

564
00:47:44,412 --> 00:47:47,172
Take my sister with you.

565
00:47:47,248 --> 00:47:49,168
-Hyeon-jung!
-Please.

566
00:48:01,012 --> 00:48:04,312
Hyeon-jung!

567
00:48:27,247 --> 00:48:30,707
<i>His friend took Hyeon-mi
and went to his uncle's house.</i>

568
00:48:30,792 --> 00:48:31,792
JI HYEON-JUNG

569
00:48:31,876 --> 00:48:34,296
<i>They recognized Hyeon-mi,</i>

570
00:48:34,379 --> 00:48:36,839
<i>so they naturally thought
the one who brought her there</i>

571
00:48:37,799 --> 00:48:39,839
<i>was Hyeon-jung.</i>

572
00:48:40,176 --> 00:48:43,136
<i>Ever since that time,
he has lived as Ji Hyeon-jung.</i>

573
00:48:49,394 --> 00:48:53,944
Ms. Jang said Hyeon-mi is the bullet
he shot his enemy with.

574
00:48:55,442 --> 00:48:59,612
Hyeon-jung always talked about his sister
with a smile on his face.

575
00:48:59,696 --> 00:49:02,196
He probably couldn't help
but loathe him as he watched

576
00:49:02,949 --> 00:49:05,199
his friend taking care
of his precious sister.

577
00:49:14,878 --> 00:49:17,798
Hyeon-jung, why are you sulking here?

578
00:49:21,509 --> 00:49:25,559
Goodness, the leaves
and flowers are all gone,

579
00:49:25,638 --> 00:49:27,308
so it looks really shabby.

580
00:49:27,599 --> 00:49:29,849
And it looks even worse
with a guy sitting here

581
00:49:29,934 --> 00:49:32,234
looking like a dog
who got caught in the rain.

582
00:49:40,862 --> 00:49:42,362
This isn't fair.

583
00:49:42,780 --> 00:49:45,950
It was really hard to see
how he got to do everything

584
00:49:46,034 --> 00:49:47,334
that I dreamed of doing.

585
00:49:50,330 --> 00:49:51,710
I'll never forgive him.

586
00:49:52,248 --> 00:49:54,918
How can you forgive someone
who punched a hole in your chest?

587
00:49:57,003 --> 00:49:58,673
Just go and hear him out.

588
00:49:59,255 --> 00:50:01,045
I'm sure he didn't come here to show off

589
00:50:01,132 --> 00:50:02,932
that he had a good life
after he killed you.

590
00:50:03,259 --> 00:50:07,009
He's probably here to tell you that
his life has been tough and harsh too.

591
00:50:10,850 --> 00:50:13,560
But it's not too bad
to hear out someone's excuses.

592
00:50:14,354 --> 00:50:15,864
You feel a little better too.

593
00:50:17,774 --> 00:50:20,574
Did that happen to you too?

594
00:50:20,860 --> 00:50:21,860
Yes.

595
00:50:23,571 --> 00:50:26,871
That's how I could finally see him off

596
00:50:27,659 --> 00:50:29,159
as he turned around and left.

597
00:50:30,537 --> 00:50:34,747
You said you didn't remember
the firefly incident.

598
00:50:36,376 --> 00:50:38,206
Are you nitpicking about my memory now?

599
00:50:39,045 --> 00:50:41,125
If you're going to sit here and sulk,

600
00:50:41,214 --> 00:50:43,094
I'll go send him away.

601
00:50:44,884 --> 00:50:47,934
Goodness, Yu-na did all that for nothing.

602
00:50:55,395 --> 00:50:58,725
It will make him feel relieved
for the rest of his life.

603
00:50:59,190 --> 00:51:00,320
However,

604
00:51:01,359 --> 00:51:03,859
since Yu-na brought him here,
go talk to him.

605
00:51:06,114 --> 00:51:10,454
A girl you like is trying very hard
to do something for you.

606
00:51:22,046 --> 00:51:23,916
I guess bringing you here

607
00:51:24,632 --> 00:51:27,052
made Hyeon-jung feel more tormented.

608
00:51:27,802 --> 00:51:29,512
Please leave.

609
00:51:30,471 --> 00:51:32,021
Well, in that case,

610
00:51:34,976 --> 00:51:36,726
can you give this to him?

611
00:51:41,232 --> 00:51:46,032
JI HYEON-JUNG

612
00:51:46,988 --> 00:51:50,238
Hyeon-jung loved going to school.

613
00:52:03,630 --> 00:52:04,800
Mr. Oh Tae-seok.

614
00:52:05,465 --> 00:52:08,755
Hyeon-jung said he will see you.

615
00:52:16,976 --> 00:52:19,146
He wants to see you in this room.

616
00:52:19,687 --> 00:52:20,767
Please go on in.

617
00:53:03,398 --> 00:53:06,398
You still look the same, Hyeon-jung.

618
00:53:08,403 --> 00:53:12,373
I kept an eye on you as you grew older.

619
00:53:13,241 --> 00:53:14,241
Tae-seok.

620
00:53:26,087 --> 00:53:27,457
OH TAE-SEOK

621
00:53:39,976 --> 00:53:42,896
JI HYEON-JUNG

622
00:53:43,187 --> 00:53:46,267
You left Hyeon-jung with his enemy.
Why aren't you worried?

623
00:53:46,899 --> 00:53:48,609
Because Hyeon-jung is good-natured.

624
00:53:49,777 --> 00:53:52,277
And he's been keeping his eye on him.

625
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:55,370
I'm sure he's already
forgiven him a little since Mr. Oh has

626
00:53:55,450 --> 00:53:57,080
never given up on Hyeon-mi.

627
00:53:57,160 --> 00:53:59,660
Since the nice Hyeon-jung
has forgiven him a little,

628
00:54:00,288 --> 00:54:03,708
the wicked owner will make him pay
the compensation.

629
00:54:06,002 --> 00:54:07,592
Are you going to take money from him?

630
00:54:08,129 --> 00:54:10,719
Hyeon-jung's friend is filthy rich.

631
00:54:12,049 --> 00:54:15,719
I should throw a party
for our little kid before he leaves.

632
00:54:19,807 --> 00:54:22,187
You donated a lot of money
and even founded a hospital

633
00:54:22,268 --> 00:54:24,098
under Ji Hyeon-jung's name.

634
00:54:24,187 --> 00:54:27,817
I've spent all my life
trying to atone for what I did.

635
00:54:29,734 --> 00:54:31,614
Then do one more thing while you're at it.

636
00:54:32,403 --> 00:54:35,953
Please buy a school
under Ji Hyeon-jung's name.

637
00:54:36,991 --> 00:54:39,621
If you can, the prestigious school
Hyeon-jung used to attend.

638
00:54:40,203 --> 00:54:41,503
Please buy it for us.

639
00:54:44,040 --> 00:54:47,250
DONGSEON HIGH SCHOOL

640
00:54:47,585 --> 00:54:49,245
We're so thankful

641
00:54:49,337 --> 00:54:53,337
Dr. Ji Hyeon-jung donated
such a large sum to the school.

642
00:54:54,258 --> 00:54:57,008
However, are you sure you're okay

643
00:54:57,094 --> 00:54:59,474
with such a small event
in the middle of the night?

644
00:54:59,555 --> 00:55:02,765
All Mr. Ji Hyeon-jung wants is
an honorary high school diploma.

645
00:55:02,850 --> 00:55:05,850
Also, the nighttime is more convenient
for those attending today.

646
00:55:06,395 --> 00:55:09,605
And the person receiving the diploma is
Ji Hyeon-jung.

647
00:55:09,690 --> 00:55:11,900
He has the same name as Dr. Ji?

648
00:55:13,319 --> 00:55:15,949
He's a student
who loved going to this school.

649
00:55:17,990 --> 00:55:19,080
There he is.

650
00:55:24,539 --> 00:55:26,369
CEREMONY FOR JI HYEON-JUNG'S
HONORARY DIPLOMA

651
00:55:26,874 --> 00:55:28,674
They must be his family.

652
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:33,090
Yes, they are.

653
00:55:39,720 --> 00:55:41,720
Is everyone here?

654
00:55:42,974 --> 00:55:45,484
Yes. So many people came.

655
00:55:51,858 --> 00:55:54,238
Why did you have to bring everyone here?

656
00:55:54,318 --> 00:55:56,898
Hyeon-jung is popular, you know.

657
00:55:57,613 --> 00:56:00,203
The Grim Reaper provided us with a bus,

658
00:56:00,283 --> 00:56:02,083
so you don't have to worry.

659
00:56:10,751 --> 00:56:13,461
Here is your honorary diploma.

660
00:56:26,601 --> 00:56:28,101
Congratulations on your graduation.

661
00:56:28,603 --> 00:56:30,153
Thank you.

662
00:56:35,401 --> 00:56:37,951
Thank you for coming, everyone.

663
00:56:45,828 --> 00:56:47,038
For...

664
00:56:47,121 --> 00:56:48,791
-Hyeon-jung!
-Hyeon-jung!

665
00:56:48,873 --> 00:56:51,503
-Thank you.
-Congratulations.

666
00:56:54,462 --> 00:56:55,462
Chan-sung.

667
00:56:55,963 --> 00:56:58,263
All of them are ghosts?

668
00:56:58,591 --> 00:57:02,051
Yes. The people you can see
have been ghosts for a long time,

669
00:57:02,136 --> 00:57:03,296
so they can show themselves.

670
00:57:03,387 --> 00:57:06,307
Show themselves?
That must be a high-level ability.

671
00:57:07,433 --> 00:57:08,603
Aside from that table,

672
00:57:08,684 --> 00:57:10,774
this whole place is
filled with our employees.

673
00:57:12,271 --> 00:57:15,231
That table is full,
and this table is full too?

674
00:57:17,318 --> 00:57:20,398
Sanchez, if this is too hard for you,
it's okay to stay outside.

675
00:57:20,488 --> 00:57:22,368
No, I'm okay.

676
00:57:22,490 --> 00:57:25,030
When else will I get to see
ghosts having dinner?

677
00:57:25,117 --> 00:57:27,037
I want to thank everyone...

678
00:57:27,787 --> 00:57:30,957
Hey, are you sure Man-wol's cousin
isn't a human?

679
00:57:31,040 --> 00:57:32,290
It's a long story.

680
00:57:32,375 --> 00:57:34,915
She was a ghost,
then she possessed someone else's body--

681
00:57:35,002 --> 00:57:36,922
Forget it. They even possess people.

682
00:57:37,004 --> 00:57:39,634
I'll look after everyone
and work even harder from now on.

683
00:57:39,715 --> 00:57:41,715
-Thank you!
-Good luck!

684
00:57:41,801 --> 00:57:44,351
-Let's go!
-Bravo.

685
00:57:47,431 --> 00:57:49,931
Chan-sung, do you like those ghosts?

686
00:57:50,268 --> 00:57:52,558
It's our first time
having a meal together.

687
00:57:52,645 --> 00:57:55,145
It feels good when you have
a meal with your colleagues, right?

688
00:57:58,150 --> 00:58:01,110
Sanchez, don't drink too much.

689
00:58:01,279 --> 00:58:03,159
Some mischievous ghosts

690
00:58:03,364 --> 00:58:05,454
like to possess drunk people.

691
00:58:06,492 --> 00:58:07,492
Are you serious?

692
00:58:09,203 --> 00:58:11,213
The one sitting at that table

693
00:58:11,580 --> 00:58:13,790
has been looking at you for a while.

694
00:58:15,167 --> 00:58:16,207
Be careful.

695
00:58:18,671 --> 00:58:22,431
Ghosts must like good-looking people
like me. Am I right?

696
00:58:39,567 --> 00:58:42,067
DASHCAM SETTINGS

697
00:58:47,575 --> 00:58:50,325
Goodness. Is that a ghost?

698
00:58:50,411 --> 00:58:52,371
I must be able to see them now.

699
00:58:57,084 --> 00:59:00,384
Here. He was recorded clearly.
It's not a ghost.

700
00:59:01,130 --> 00:59:02,510
You startled me.

701
00:59:03,382 --> 00:59:04,762
I guess he's not a ghost.

702
00:59:05,885 --> 00:59:09,505
There's no need to be so scared.
Ghosts used to be people too.

703
00:59:09,805 --> 00:59:12,845
It's normal to be scared.
You're the one who became strange.

704
00:59:14,810 --> 00:59:17,860
Chan-sung, I think you're going too far.

705
00:59:18,189 --> 00:59:21,229
I'm worried you might completely move on
to the other side.

706
00:59:22,610 --> 00:59:24,820
I understand your concern,

707
00:59:25,613 --> 00:59:28,663
but the people
you saw today are all going to leave.

708
00:59:29,533 --> 00:59:30,623
Man-wol, too?

709
00:59:33,120 --> 00:59:34,160
Yes.

710
00:59:35,581 --> 00:59:36,791
Jang Man-wol, too.

711
00:59:48,219 --> 00:59:49,929
I gave Mr. Koo the medicine

712
00:59:50,304 --> 00:59:52,524
while you were away.

713
01:00:00,064 --> 01:00:01,524
He didn't take it.

714
01:00:03,150 --> 01:00:04,280
I see.

715
01:00:05,027 --> 01:00:07,357
Mr. Koo must have trusted

716
01:00:07,446 --> 01:00:09,026
you'd return.

717
01:00:13,577 --> 01:00:15,407
I guess you didn't.

718
01:00:15,746 --> 01:00:18,866
I was glad you were freed from this place.

719
01:00:19,458 --> 01:00:20,458
But,

720
01:00:21,585 --> 01:00:22,995
you returned.

721
01:00:23,629 --> 01:00:26,259
I didn't return because I'm tied
to the Moon Tree like before.

722
01:00:27,925 --> 01:00:30,085
A new owner will be coming.

723
01:00:30,761 --> 01:00:32,471
Mago is working on it.

724
01:00:33,347 --> 01:00:36,017
Does Mr. Koo know about this?

725
01:00:37,268 --> 01:00:40,188
Yes. He does.

726
01:00:41,397 --> 01:00:43,017
Although neither of us talks about it.

727
01:00:45,901 --> 01:00:49,411
I want to send off Mr. Kim,
Hyeon-jung, and you

728
01:00:51,031 --> 01:00:53,281
while I'm here.

729
01:00:54,827 --> 01:00:55,907
But...

730
01:00:58,122 --> 01:00:59,752
I'm not sure if I will have enough time.

731
01:01:18,976 --> 01:01:21,346
Ms. Jang is inside.

732
01:01:21,729 --> 01:01:22,859
Ms. Choe.

733
01:01:23,564 --> 01:01:25,234
I paid a visit to that woman

734
01:01:25,774 --> 01:01:27,574
we found at the pharmacy,

735
01:01:27,943 --> 01:01:29,703
and she'll be giving birth soon.

736
01:01:31,322 --> 01:01:34,332
If the baby ends up carrying on
the family name,

737
01:01:36,785 --> 01:01:38,405
will you continue to stay behind?

738
01:01:41,290 --> 01:01:42,920
Are you afraid

739
01:01:43,250 --> 01:01:44,880
that I'd wander around

740
01:01:44,960 --> 01:01:46,630
after Ms. Jang is gone

741
01:01:47,338 --> 01:01:49,128
and Hotel del Luna disappears?

742
01:01:50,799 --> 01:01:52,129
So you know.

743
01:01:53,385 --> 01:01:55,215
I just found out.

744
01:01:56,805 --> 01:02:00,935
Ms. Jang is no longer tied down
to the Moon Tree.

745
01:02:01,519 --> 01:02:05,269
She could have gone
to the afterlife if she wanted.

746
01:02:06,941 --> 01:02:10,531
What has her tied down here must be you,

747
01:02:11,362 --> 01:02:13,112
Mr. Koo.

748
01:02:13,989 --> 01:02:15,949
Are you worried that I'd become

749
01:02:16,659 --> 01:02:18,119
another Moon Tree?

750
01:02:18,994 --> 01:02:20,504
I'm reminded of something

751
01:02:20,996 --> 01:02:24,166
Mago said to that bride

752
01:02:24,291 --> 01:02:27,131
who had a ghost wedding here.

753
01:02:27,920 --> 01:02:29,550
She said that

754
01:02:30,506 --> 01:02:33,836
it's hard, but sometimes
it's easier to let go than hold on.

755
01:03:00,953 --> 01:03:04,753
Gosh, it's so heavy. It's so heavy.

756
01:03:13,507 --> 01:03:14,467
What are these?

757
01:03:14,550 --> 01:03:17,340
I take them out from time to time.

758
01:03:17,636 --> 01:03:20,056
There's so much dust.

759
01:03:27,104 --> 01:03:29,734
It's so strong. Open it.

760
01:03:43,662 --> 01:03:45,252
-It's a camera.
-Yes.

761
01:03:45,831 --> 01:03:50,751
I used it to take all these pictures.

762
01:03:52,463 --> 01:03:53,763
It looks quite old.

763
01:03:55,007 --> 01:03:57,967
Did your previous managers
take those pictures for you?

764
01:03:58,052 --> 01:03:59,762
Let's see...

765
01:04:00,804 --> 01:04:03,524
That's the one. The one
who took this photo of Man-wol Hostel

766
01:04:03,599 --> 01:04:05,599
ran away after using up all of my money.

767
01:04:05,893 --> 01:04:09,483
So I chased after him, and it turned out
his wife was close to giving birth.

768
01:04:09,855 --> 01:04:11,145
I just let him go.

769
01:04:12,107 --> 01:04:15,527
You already know Hwang Mun-suk
from Hotel del Luna.

770
01:04:15,653 --> 01:04:18,533
And way before this one...

771
01:04:18,697 --> 01:04:19,617
There it is.

772
01:04:21,283 --> 01:04:25,503
The manager at that time was
really handsome.

773
01:04:26,580 --> 01:04:28,670
They say if a man is handsome,
you should call him honey.

774
01:04:28,749 --> 01:04:31,249
He was more than just a honey.

775
01:04:32,294 --> 01:04:33,554
I don't believe you.

776
01:04:34,505 --> 01:04:36,415
Mr. Kim told me everything.

777
01:04:36,507 --> 01:04:38,757
Of all the managers
he saw in the last 500 years,

778
01:04:39,718 --> 01:04:42,678
I'm the most handsome one.

779
01:04:44,348 --> 01:04:47,688
He told me you fell in love with me
because of my looks.

780
01:04:48,852 --> 01:04:50,902
Why would you talk about such a thing
with Mr. Kim?

781
01:04:50,979 --> 01:04:52,859
When did you two get so close?

782
01:04:53,524 --> 01:04:56,074
That's why you should've taken
these pictures

783
01:04:56,151 --> 01:04:58,071
with the people who were with you
at that time.

784
01:04:58,153 --> 01:04:59,743
Then you'd have a proof.

785
01:05:00,614 --> 01:05:01,744
Back then,

786
01:05:02,533 --> 01:05:05,913
I thought they were just passing me by
and meant nothing to me.

787
01:05:06,453 --> 01:05:10,423
But looking at these with you,

788
01:05:11,583 --> 01:05:15,423
it's too bad I didn't leave
any records behind.

789
01:05:18,173 --> 01:05:19,883
Would you like to leave a record right now

790
01:05:20,634 --> 01:05:21,844
with that camera?

791
01:05:26,890 --> 01:05:30,390
Hyeon-jung got his honorary diploma,
but he didn't get to take any pictures.

792
01:05:30,686 --> 01:05:32,806
We should all get together
to take a picture.

793
01:05:33,021 --> 01:05:34,191
I'll take it for you.

794
01:05:52,332 --> 01:05:55,592
I've never taken a picture before.
I wonder if I'll be visible.

795
01:05:55,669 --> 01:05:58,799
You will. I took a picture
with a phone before.

796
01:05:59,423 --> 01:06:02,223
We should have put on more blush.

797
01:06:02,301 --> 01:06:04,221
We look pale like ghosts.

798
01:06:04,970 --> 01:06:06,310
It's okay.

799
01:06:06,388 --> 01:06:08,678
What's so wrong with looking like ghosts
when we're ghosts?

800
01:06:09,391 --> 01:06:12,561
Hyeon-jung, don't open your mouth
when we take the picture.

801
01:06:12,644 --> 01:06:15,484
Mr. Kim, don't blink.

802
01:06:20,736 --> 01:06:21,776
All right.

803
01:06:22,821 --> 01:06:23,951
I'll take it now.

804
01:06:24,448 --> 01:06:27,868
One, two, three...

805
01:06:40,255 --> 01:06:41,835
Mr. Koo, you should join us.

806
01:06:41,924 --> 01:06:43,304
Yes, hurry over.

807
01:06:43,383 --> 01:06:45,053
Come over, Mr. Koo.

808
01:07:24,925 --> 01:07:26,795
How can I put it away
when you're sitting on it?

809
01:07:27,469 --> 01:07:28,429
Get off now.

810
01:07:29,847 --> 01:07:31,307
Lift me off of it.

811
01:07:33,600 --> 01:07:36,770
Just try it.
I won't move until you lift me.

812
01:07:37,145 --> 01:07:39,685
Forget it. You can put it away then.

813
01:07:46,280 --> 01:07:48,410
To the room.

814
01:08:02,963 --> 01:08:05,723
We took a picture.
Now, let's go eat <i>jajangmyeon</i>.

815
01:08:09,720 --> 01:08:10,800
Darn it.

816
01:08:15,726 --> 01:08:17,016
You took a picture.

817
01:08:17,644 --> 01:08:19,484
It was a lot of fun.

818
01:08:21,273 --> 01:08:22,653
Why didn't you call me?

819
01:08:22,941 --> 01:08:26,951
We took it with Mr. Koo
to remember this moment

820
01:08:27,070 --> 01:08:29,990
before Ms. Jang leaves
and the hotel disappears.

821
01:08:30,240 --> 01:08:32,660
Is the hotel going to disappear? Why?

822
01:08:32,910 --> 01:08:37,830
Mago is preparing to make
a new Guest House of the Moon.

823
01:08:39,583 --> 01:08:42,923
Then Ms. Jang's Hotel del Luna

824
01:08:43,754 --> 01:08:44,924
will disappear.

825
01:08:45,172 --> 01:08:46,212
What about you?

826
01:08:47,466 --> 01:08:50,676
Are you going to leave
if the hotel disappears?

827
01:09:22,459 --> 01:09:24,919
It's fermenting really well.

828
01:09:27,381 --> 01:09:31,471
<i>I heard Mago is preparing
the wine for the next hotel owner.</i>

829
01:09:32,260 --> 01:09:33,850
I'll drink it and become the owner.

830
01:09:33,929 --> 01:09:36,519
It's Mago who decides the next owner.

831
01:09:36,598 --> 01:09:39,888
Then Ms. Jang should drink it
and continue to be the owner.

832
01:09:39,977 --> 01:09:42,937
Do you think Mago would do that?
After everything that's happened?

833
01:09:44,147 --> 01:09:45,517
When is Mago coming?

834
01:09:45,607 --> 01:09:46,687
Where can I find her?

835
01:09:46,775 --> 01:09:50,025
She's not someone you can meet
just because you want to.

836
01:09:50,112 --> 01:09:52,282
Then nobody here can meet with her?

837
01:09:53,657 --> 01:09:57,577
I think Mr. Koo has the permission
to enter Mago's pharmacy.

838
01:09:57,661 --> 01:10:01,371
He said he brought the firefly
from her shop.

839
01:10:26,314 --> 01:10:28,284
PHARMACY
11-28 YAKJAE-GOLMOK, GYEONGDONG MARKET

840
01:10:32,571 --> 01:10:34,241
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

841
01:10:38,118 --> 01:10:40,328
Sanchez, thank you for everything.

842
01:10:40,620 --> 01:10:43,670
Let's go out to eat with Chan-sung soon.
It'll be my treat.

843
01:10:43,749 --> 01:10:45,499
Are you moving back
to your parents' house?

844
01:10:46,376 --> 01:10:47,586
She's moving in with me.

845
01:10:48,295 --> 01:10:49,915
Are you going to live together?

846
01:10:50,756 --> 01:10:52,586
It's going to be so tough for you,
Yeong-su.

847
01:10:53,216 --> 01:10:55,886
Mi-ra tries to help around the house,

848
01:10:55,969 --> 01:10:57,429
but she's useless.

849
01:10:58,430 --> 01:10:59,890
I already know.

850
01:11:00,182 --> 01:11:01,932
We had so many fights,

851
01:11:02,017 --> 01:11:05,517
so we decided to see
how much more we can fight.

852
01:11:05,771 --> 01:11:08,571
Luckily, I'm good at cleaning.

853
01:11:08,648 --> 01:11:12,358
And she's better at cooking than me,
if nothing else.

854
01:11:14,029 --> 01:11:14,989
She is?

855
01:11:15,280 --> 01:11:16,110
Yes.

856
01:11:17,032 --> 01:11:20,702
The kimchi and side dishes
she brought me were good.

857
01:11:21,578 --> 01:11:24,458
I didn't make them all by myself.

858
01:11:24,664 --> 01:11:26,544
My parents helped me a little.

859
01:11:26,625 --> 01:11:27,825
I see.

860
01:11:27,918 --> 01:11:31,048
It's not a lie since they make them
at the factory.

861
01:11:31,129 --> 01:11:32,459
"The factory"?

862
01:11:33,673 --> 01:11:36,933
My parents run a kimchi factory.

863
01:11:37,844 --> 01:11:40,854
They're always on the shopping channel.
Haven't you heard of Daeho Kimchi?

864
01:11:40,931 --> 01:11:42,681
"Daeho Kimchi"?

865
01:11:42,766 --> 01:11:46,056
I used to eat it all the time
back in the day.

866
01:11:47,104 --> 01:11:51,154
Is that why Mi-ra's side dishes
were perfect to my taste?

867
01:11:51,441 --> 01:11:52,691
No wonder.

868
01:11:52,901 --> 01:11:56,611
The food that raised you
was made by my parents.

869
01:11:57,823 --> 01:11:59,833
We're meant to be together.

870
01:11:59,908 --> 01:12:01,368
I think so.

871
01:12:01,451 --> 01:12:04,291
Chan-sung and I ate that kimchi too.

872
01:12:04,371 --> 01:12:06,831
It's a kimchi brand
that fed countless people in Korea.

873
01:12:06,915 --> 01:12:08,995
I don't think it's anything special.

874
01:12:09,084 --> 01:12:11,594
Yeong-su says it's perfect to his taste.

875
01:12:11,670 --> 01:12:13,670
-Right?
-Sure.

876
01:12:13,755 --> 01:12:15,165
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

877
01:12:15,465 --> 01:12:17,295
-Love shot?
-Love shot.

878
01:12:17,384 --> 01:12:18,764
You read my mind.

879
01:12:21,596 --> 01:12:24,216
They should get along
until they move in together.

880
01:12:24,307 --> 01:12:26,517
She might end up staying here
if they fight.

881
01:12:29,855 --> 01:12:30,685
Is it good?

882
01:12:30,772 --> 01:12:31,732
It's good.

883
01:12:35,610 --> 01:12:37,990
Both of you are writers, aren't you?

884
01:12:38,071 --> 01:12:41,121
This was Li Bai's favorite drink.

885
01:12:42,409 --> 01:12:46,079
He's a famous best-selling author.

886
01:12:46,163 --> 01:12:48,673
He passed away
just before the release of his new book.

887
01:12:48,748 --> 01:12:50,458
It's really unfortunate.

888
01:12:50,750 --> 01:12:52,790
I did a lot of research,

889
01:12:52,878 --> 01:12:54,588
and the story was really interesting.

890
01:12:55,046 --> 01:12:56,716
What is your novel about?

891
01:12:56,798 --> 01:12:59,508
It's about a scholar
from the Joseon Dynasty.

892
01:13:00,677 --> 01:13:02,097
The bartender is a scholar

893
01:13:02,179 --> 01:13:04,599
who won the first place
in the National State Exam.

894
01:13:05,015 --> 01:13:06,515
Really?

895
01:13:06,600 --> 01:13:08,690
What is your name?

896
01:13:08,768 --> 01:13:11,398
My name wasn't recorded anywhere
in history.

897
01:13:11,479 --> 01:13:14,269
The protagonist of the novel
I was writing is also someone

898
01:13:14,357 --> 01:13:16,897
who won the first place
in the National State Exam.

899
01:13:16,985 --> 01:13:20,105
But his appointment got cancelled.

900
01:13:20,197 --> 01:13:22,027
Did that actually happen?

901
01:13:22,115 --> 01:13:24,365
He got caught for writing lewd literature,

902
01:13:24,451 --> 01:13:27,951
so he was beaten up by other scholars,
and his appointment got cancelled.

903
01:13:28,038 --> 01:13:29,828
It's the story of a perverted scholar.

904
01:13:31,208 --> 01:13:32,578
That's interesting.

905
01:13:33,376 --> 01:13:35,836
What's the name of that perverted scholar?

906
01:13:35,962 --> 01:13:37,552
He has a grandiose name.

907
01:13:37,631 --> 01:13:40,131
It's Si-ik, which means
the wings of the era.

908
01:13:40,592 --> 01:13:42,892
His name is Kim Si-ik.

909
01:13:48,975 --> 01:13:50,305
<i>Kim Si-ik!</i>

910
01:13:51,019 --> 01:13:52,479
<i>If you have any shame,</i>

911
01:13:52,562 --> 01:13:55,442
<i>do not ever dare lift up your face again.</i>

912
01:13:58,693 --> 01:14:01,283
I had finished the novel before I died,

913
01:14:01,363 --> 01:14:04,073
so it might be published
as my posthumous work.

914
01:14:04,699 --> 01:14:06,869
I hope it does get published.

915
01:14:34,896 --> 01:14:38,646
<i>I heard the wine is made
with the energy of the moon.</i>

916
01:14:45,991 --> 01:14:48,701
The tree came back
to how it used to look like.

917
01:14:49,494 --> 01:14:52,164
No, it's different from that time.

918
01:14:52,747 --> 01:14:55,247
Back then, it was just on display.

919
01:14:55,917 --> 01:14:59,247
But this time, its leaves sprouted,
and its flowers bloomed and fell

920
01:14:59,337 --> 01:15:00,837
as time passed once again.

921
01:15:01,131 --> 01:15:03,301
The tree has gone through all that.

922
01:15:05,844 --> 01:15:09,014
Do you hope to see it

923
01:15:09,097 --> 01:15:12,177
grow out leaves and bloom flowers again?

924
01:15:19,316 --> 01:15:20,776
This is dead.

925
01:15:22,027 --> 01:15:24,147
If I wish to have such time once again,

926
01:15:25,613 --> 01:15:27,243
I should probably cross the bridge.

927
01:15:28,783 --> 01:15:30,123
Probably.

928
01:15:33,204 --> 01:15:36,084
Yu-na, what's wrong?

929
01:15:39,377 --> 01:15:40,497
Ms. Jang.

930
01:15:40,962 --> 01:15:44,882
I stole this wine from Mago's pharmacy.

931
01:15:50,805 --> 01:15:53,175
I heard it's for the new owner.

932
01:15:55,477 --> 01:15:57,807
Can you drink this

933
01:15:59,064 --> 01:16:01,024
and stay at this hotel?

934
01:16:26,508 --> 01:16:29,258
A girl who has been
coming in and out of your hotel

935
01:16:29,344 --> 01:16:32,184
stole the wine I made.

936
01:16:32,847 --> 01:16:35,677
I'm sure she did this
because she was afraid

937
01:16:35,767 --> 01:16:37,347
the reception guy,
Hyeon-jung, would leave.

938
01:16:37,560 --> 01:16:39,650
She didn't want the hotel to disappear.

939
01:16:39,729 --> 01:16:43,859
Then she probably brought that to Man-wol.

940
01:16:47,278 --> 01:16:49,738
If she drinks that

941
01:16:49,823 --> 01:16:52,283
and regains the power of the Moon Tree,

942
01:16:52,367 --> 01:16:54,327
Hotel del Luna will remain here,

943
01:16:56,329 --> 01:16:57,749
and you two

944
01:16:58,373 --> 01:17:00,883
can be together again.

945
01:17:04,921 --> 01:17:06,971
If Ms. Jang makes such a choice,

946
01:17:08,049 --> 01:17:09,429
will you not stop her?

947
01:17:12,303 --> 01:17:14,513
You wanted to let her go peacefully.

948
01:17:17,600 --> 01:17:19,690
If I do not stop her,

949
01:17:20,728 --> 01:17:23,648
what will you do?

950
01:17:40,248 --> 01:17:41,998
Mr. Koo, Yu-na came with...

951
01:17:42,083 --> 01:17:45,043
I know. Where's Jang Man-wol?

952
01:18:11,446 --> 01:18:14,566
On the first day that I was
tied down to the Moon Tree,

953
01:18:17,368 --> 01:18:20,248
the full moon was
as big and bright as that one.

954
01:18:28,171 --> 01:18:32,131
The wine I drank then
fell into my hands again.

955
01:18:37,597 --> 01:18:38,717
Chan-sung.

956
01:18:43,561 --> 01:18:45,611
Should I drink this again?

957
01:19:00,078 --> 01:19:01,828
When I went back in time

958
01:19:03,373 --> 01:19:05,003
and met you,

959
01:19:05,875 --> 01:19:08,035
I wanted to take the drink you offered me

960
01:19:08,628 --> 01:19:10,628
to stay with you there.

961
01:19:16,553 --> 01:19:18,013
<i>If I had done that,</i>

962
01:19:18,930 --> 01:19:21,180
<i>I would've become
the 85th human who worked for you,</i>

963
01:19:22,475 --> 01:19:25,095
<i>and drawn a portrait of you.</i>

964
01:19:41,452 --> 01:19:44,122
<i>I had this thought as I hung
the picture we took together.</i>

965
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:51,300
<i>That I will be your last manager,
the 99th one.</i>

966
01:19:53,548 --> 01:19:54,798
<i>I won't let you</i>

967
01:19:55,216 --> 01:19:58,596
<i>spend meaningless time with the 100th one.</i>

968
01:20:11,566 --> 01:20:12,686
So...

969
01:20:16,029 --> 01:20:17,449
don't drink that.

970
01:20:28,041 --> 01:20:30,751
I knew you would say that.

971
01:21:44,784 --> 01:21:46,624
Thank you, Chan-sung.

972
01:22:01,384 --> 01:22:02,844
I love you.

973
01:22:15,690 --> 01:22:17,230
I love you.

974
01:23:15,625 --> 01:23:17,745
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

975
01:23:49,199 --> 01:23:50,989
It's a little kid.

976
01:23:58,166 --> 01:23:59,666
It seems like her parents

977
01:23:59,751 --> 01:24:03,301
already crossed the Samdo River.

978
01:24:03,839 --> 01:24:08,889
How did this little girl manage
to stay alive for so long?

979
01:24:09,011 --> 01:24:10,511
When I came to take her,

980
01:24:10,679 --> 01:24:13,139
I was also surprised to see
that she was still alive.

981
01:24:14,516 --> 01:24:17,226
This little girl is trying so hard
to stay alive.

982
01:24:17,311 --> 01:24:19,351
Why don't you take a step back?

983
01:24:20,063 --> 01:24:23,233
But she won't last more than a few hours.

984
01:24:23,817 --> 01:24:25,817
You never know

985
01:24:27,029 --> 01:24:29,529
what might happen
in that short amount of time.

986
01:24:52,846 --> 01:24:55,426
Father, I see something over there.

987
01:24:55,515 --> 01:24:56,515
What?

988
01:24:59,102 --> 01:25:00,312
My gosh.

989
01:25:02,814 --> 01:25:05,784
Hey, it's very dirty.
Don't touch anything.

990
01:25:06,276 --> 01:25:07,736
They're dead.

991
01:25:08,028 --> 01:25:09,448
They must be from Goguryeo.

992
01:25:09,571 --> 01:25:12,821
I think they were killed while wandering
around after their country collapsed.

993
01:25:13,116 --> 01:25:14,276
Let me see.

994
01:25:14,660 --> 01:25:17,080
Let's take the wagon.

995
01:25:17,788 --> 01:25:20,458
Thank you for the wagon. My goodness.

996
01:25:40,685 --> 01:25:41,805
She moved.

997
01:25:48,693 --> 01:25:49,993
Can you see me?

998
01:25:53,865 --> 01:25:55,195
You're alive.

999
01:26:03,667 --> 01:26:04,997
Don't be sad.

1000
01:26:05,544 --> 01:26:09,464
I'm sure your parents went
to the Guest House of the Moon.

1001
01:26:10,966 --> 01:26:12,836
I heard it from a granny
who sells medicine.

1002
01:26:13,135 --> 01:26:14,965
There's a place called
the Guest House of the Moon

1003
01:26:15,053 --> 01:26:16,563
somewhere in the wilderness.

1004
01:26:18,140 --> 01:26:22,060
It's where dead people go to get some rest
before they leave for the afterlife.

1005
01:26:23,395 --> 01:26:24,895
What's your name?

1006
01:26:41,079 --> 01:26:42,409
Man-wol.

1007
01:26:45,542 --> 01:26:46,592
The moon.

1008
01:26:47,502 --> 01:26:48,882
Your name means the "full moon."

1009
01:26:51,506 --> 01:26:52,626
It's pretty.

1010
01:26:57,012 --> 01:26:58,262
Do you think

1011
01:26:59,389 --> 01:27:03,099
we already met in our past lives?

1012
01:27:07,522 --> 01:27:09,902
I'm 1,300 years old.

1013
01:27:11,401 --> 01:27:13,491
I wonder how I got to meet you now.

1014
01:27:16,031 --> 01:27:18,031
Sometimes, it takes 1,300 years

1015
01:27:18,366 --> 01:27:20,236
for two people to meet each other.

1016
01:27:25,123 --> 01:27:26,333
Do you know

1017
01:27:26,666 --> 01:27:28,626
that it takes a very long time

1018
01:27:29,294 --> 01:27:31,214
for the light from the stars to reach us?

1019
01:27:34,132 --> 01:27:38,262
The Orion Nebula is
1,300 lightyears away from Earth.

1020
01:27:38,595 --> 01:27:40,635
That means it takes 1,300 years

1021
01:27:42,390 --> 01:27:44,940
for us to be able to see it
with our own eyes.

1022
01:27:46,561 --> 01:27:47,601
Really?

1023
01:27:48,104 --> 01:27:49,564
Where is it right now?

1024
01:27:52,609 --> 01:27:56,149
You can only see it during winter,
so you can't see it right now.

1025
01:27:59,449 --> 01:28:00,619
Winter?

1026
01:28:01,785 --> 01:28:04,195
Starting from the next full moon,

1027
01:28:04,329 --> 01:28:07,539
the energy of the moon
will be withdrawn from this place.

1028
01:28:08,416 --> 01:28:12,456
From now on, you won't be
getting any new guests.

1029
01:28:13,088 --> 01:28:14,918
I guess you're telling me
to close it down.

1030
01:28:15,298 --> 01:28:17,378
Your Guest House of the Moon...

1031
01:28:20,720 --> 01:28:22,180
will only exist

1032
01:28:23,306 --> 01:28:24,976
up until the next full moon.

1033
01:28:29,104 --> 01:28:31,574
It's a pity that we can only see it

1034
01:28:32,524 --> 01:28:33,694
in winter.

1035
01:28:35,986 --> 01:28:38,146
Chan-sung, is there any star
we can see right now

1036
01:28:38,238 --> 01:28:39,858
instead of the Orion Nebula?

1037
01:28:40,115 --> 01:28:41,615
Well...

1038
01:28:43,285 --> 01:28:46,325
I'm not sure.
I'm not very good with astronomy.

1039
01:28:46,413 --> 01:28:47,753
So I can't answer that question.

1040
01:28:51,251 --> 01:28:53,001
You dumbhead from Harvard.

1041
01:28:53,086 --> 01:28:54,546
You could've just pointed

1042
01:28:54,629 --> 01:28:57,219
at any one of those stars in the sky.

1043
01:28:57,299 --> 01:29:00,679
Do you think I would've corrected you
if you were wrong?

1044
01:29:00,969 --> 01:29:03,639
I would've just acted
like I was impressed.

1045
01:29:08,143 --> 01:29:08,983
Shall I, then?

1046
01:29:09,561 --> 01:29:12,311
Let's see.
I should pick a beautiful, shining one

1047
01:29:12,397 --> 01:29:14,187
since you like shiny things.

1048
01:29:14,274 --> 01:29:15,694
Forget it. It's too late.

1049
01:29:22,240 --> 01:29:23,910
There really is one more.

1050
01:29:24,117 --> 01:29:26,657
Another star you can see
after living through 1,300 years.

1051
01:29:29,873 --> 01:29:30,963
Me, Koo Chan-sung.

1052
01:29:33,418 --> 01:29:35,418
I told you my name means a brilliant star.

1053
01:29:40,842 --> 01:29:43,682
All right. You're all I need.

1054
01:29:44,387 --> 01:29:47,217
I don't care about the star
that I can only see in winter.

1055
01:29:49,935 --> 01:29:52,015
I'll be happy as long as I can see you.

1056
01:29:56,858 --> 01:30:00,318
Look at you, Chan-sung.
You shine so brightly.

1057
01:30:00,403 --> 01:30:02,283
Twinkle twinkle! I'm so dazzled!

1058
01:30:05,325 --> 01:30:07,285
Look at you, Man-wol.

1059
01:30:07,369 --> 01:30:09,539
You're looking so bright
like the full moon.

1060
01:30:09,704 --> 01:30:10,794
"The full moon"?

1061
01:30:10,872 --> 01:30:12,332
Or we could call you my lucky charm.

1062
01:30:12,415 --> 01:30:14,875
You deserve the nickname
as you've gotten much nicer.

1063
01:30:15,752 --> 01:30:17,842
You said I'd be reincarnated as a pig.

1064
01:30:17,921 --> 01:30:20,221
You said you'd happily be
reincarnated as chicken noodles.

1065
01:30:21,508 --> 01:30:23,678
What if that actually happens?

1066
01:30:25,345 --> 01:30:28,215
It's okay. I'll be the fresh kimchi
that goes with it.

1067
01:30:29,933 --> 01:30:30,813
Really?

1068
01:30:31,601 --> 01:30:33,191
-Seriously?
-Yes.

1069
01:30:34,270 --> 01:30:35,610
-You really mean it, right?
-Yes.

1070
01:30:35,689 --> 01:30:38,149
You said you'd be the fresh kimchi.
You promised me.

1071
01:30:38,233 --> 01:30:40,113
Yes, I'll really be
the fresh kimchi for you.

1072
01:31:11,307 --> 01:31:13,807
Did Mr. Kim go somewhere?

1073
01:31:14,602 --> 01:31:17,692
He went out after chatting
with those guests.

1074
01:31:17,939 --> 01:31:18,939
Yes.

1075
01:31:22,193 --> 01:31:23,573
Where did he go?

1076
01:31:25,947 --> 01:31:27,487
My new novel will be released.

1077
01:31:27,574 --> 01:31:29,334
It's about a perverted scholar, Kim Si-ik,

1078
01:31:29,409 --> 01:31:31,329
who passed the National State Exam
for nothing.

1079
01:31:32,662 --> 01:31:36,502
I should just leave before I must face
such humiliation.

1080
01:31:36,916 --> 01:31:38,036
I should really leave.

1081
01:31:44,340 --> 01:31:47,090
Let's not forget to say goodbye
to each other before we leave.

1082
01:31:47,177 --> 01:31:49,717
Don't leave without saying anything.
I'm serious.

1083
01:31:51,306 --> 01:31:52,306
Gosh.

1084
01:31:54,434 --> 01:31:56,274
Oh, dear.

1085
01:32:01,483 --> 01:32:04,113
Ms. Jang, I can't find Mr. Kim anywhere.

1086
01:32:04,194 --> 01:32:06,404
-He's probably with Hyeon-jung.
-No, he's not.

1087
01:32:06,488 --> 01:32:08,658
I couldn't find him anywhere in the hotel.

1088
01:32:08,740 --> 01:32:09,990
Maybe he stepped out.

1089
01:32:10,075 --> 01:32:12,945
He rarely goes outside the hotel.

1090
01:32:13,036 --> 01:32:14,696
Even when he does, he never leaves alone.

1091
01:32:14,788 --> 01:32:17,248
He still sounds like a man
living in the Joseon era, you know.

1092
01:32:17,332 --> 01:32:18,672
Apparently, he turned pale

1093
01:32:18,750 --> 01:32:21,130
and left the bar
while chatting with some guests

1094
01:32:21,211 --> 01:32:23,341
about a scholar
who aced the National State Exam.

1095
01:32:24,255 --> 01:32:26,255
A scholar
who aced the National State Exam?

1096
01:32:26,341 --> 01:32:29,891
You know about his situation, right?

1097
01:32:30,762 --> 01:32:34,222
By any chance, was his name

1098
01:32:35,683 --> 01:32:37,773
Kim Si-ik when he was alive?

1099
01:32:40,188 --> 01:32:44,228
Who is the guest that spoke ill

1100
01:32:44,984 --> 01:32:46,194
of Kim Seon-bi?

1101
01:32:47,987 --> 01:32:51,317
I was telling him that I died
before I could publish

1102
01:32:51,407 --> 01:32:54,617
the book I wrote
about the scholar, Kim Si-ik.

1103
01:32:54,702 --> 01:32:57,412
And the novel mocks Kim Si-ik, doesn't it?

1104
01:32:57,497 --> 01:33:01,037
It's a fiction I wrote
based on thorough research.

1105
01:33:01,126 --> 01:33:04,416
So that novel will actually be released?

1106
01:33:04,963 --> 01:33:08,513
I already sent the manuscript
to my publisher.

1107
01:33:08,591 --> 01:33:12,181
They'll publish it as my posthumous work.

1108
01:33:12,887 --> 01:33:15,467
Which publisher did you send it to?

1109
01:33:15,557 --> 01:33:17,387
And how many people have read this?

1110
01:33:17,642 --> 01:33:20,942
I still write a novel in longhand,

1111
01:33:21,020 --> 01:33:22,980
so there's only one manuscript.

1112
01:33:23,064 --> 01:33:25,904
I'm sure the editor-in-chief is
the only one who's read it.

1113
01:33:30,238 --> 01:33:32,238
I must find this publisher.

1114
01:33:41,291 --> 01:33:43,291
His handwriting is so bad as always.

1115
01:33:44,377 --> 01:33:45,797
Gosh, my eyes hurt.

1116
01:33:47,130 --> 01:33:49,550
SALACIOUS SCHOLAR, KIM SI-IK

1117
01:33:51,509 --> 01:33:53,219
Is the air conditioner on?

1118
01:33:54,470 --> 01:33:56,680
HAEGONG PUBLISHING COMPANY

1119
01:34:00,101 --> 01:34:02,981
I am not a salacious scholar.

1120
01:34:03,855 --> 01:34:05,225
This isn't fair.

1121
01:34:12,363 --> 01:34:14,453
First, try to buy the manuscript from him.

1122
01:34:14,657 --> 01:34:16,947
The money from selling the horses
will be enough.

1123
01:34:17,035 --> 01:34:19,495
But I'm worried Mr. Kim
might cause trouble before we do that.

1124
01:34:19,746 --> 01:34:21,246
If he does anything to harm humans,

1125
01:34:21,331 --> 01:34:23,461
the Grim Reaper won't let it slide.

1126
01:34:24,876 --> 01:34:27,916
Kim Seon-bi is like a crane.

1127
01:34:28,004 --> 01:34:29,764
Have you seen a crane attacking humans?

1128
01:34:30,506 --> 01:34:32,216
He won't harm anyone.

1129
01:34:32,300 --> 01:34:34,590
Still, he's been holding a grudge
for 500 years.

1130
01:34:34,677 --> 01:34:36,177
Cranes make sure their feathers stay

1131
01:34:36,262 --> 01:34:38,512
as white as snow
even when they're standing in mud.

1132
01:34:38,848 --> 01:34:42,308
Seon-bi has waited for 500 years

1133
01:34:42,852 --> 01:34:44,402
to clear his name.

1134
01:35:00,370 --> 01:35:02,410
I AM NOT SALACIOUS

1135
01:35:14,258 --> 01:35:18,348
I'm Kim Si-ik. I am not salacious.

1136
01:35:25,520 --> 01:35:27,110
I scared him too much.

1137
01:35:27,355 --> 01:35:29,605
I just want to make sure
the book won't be published.

1138
01:35:31,401 --> 01:35:33,491
Should I have gone easy on him?

1139
01:35:37,657 --> 01:35:39,117
Sir!

1140
01:35:39,951 --> 01:35:41,121
What's wrong?

1141
01:35:41,202 --> 01:35:42,332
I saw a ghost.

1142
01:35:42,578 --> 01:35:43,908
-Sorry?
-A ghost?

1143
01:35:44,330 --> 01:35:47,290
I just saw the ghost of Kim Si-ik.

1144
01:35:48,459 --> 01:35:49,919
-Hold on.
-You saw his ghost?

1145
01:35:50,003 --> 01:35:52,463
-It means the book will be a hit!
-We will hit the jackpot!

1146
01:35:52,880 --> 01:35:54,420
My gosh, sir!

1147
01:35:54,507 --> 01:35:57,927
-I was really scared.
-What a lucky dream!

1148
01:35:58,011 --> 01:36:00,261
It wasn't a dream.
I really saw him, you fool!

1149
01:36:00,346 --> 01:36:02,466
-Are we celebrating tonight?
-A team dinner will be nice!

1150
01:36:02,557 --> 01:36:04,517
-Guys, how about sushi?
-My gosh.

1151
01:36:14,902 --> 01:36:16,072
Mr. Kim.

1152
01:36:16,904 --> 01:36:20,534
Mr. Koo, Ms. Jang. You knew I'd be here?

1153
01:36:20,616 --> 01:36:22,076
Look at yourself.

1154
01:36:22,160 --> 01:36:23,700
Let's go back to the hotel for now.

1155
01:36:23,786 --> 01:36:26,786
I cannot go back to the hotel
for I am too humiliated.

1156
01:36:27,290 --> 01:36:30,710
I'll just take the bus here
and head to the afterlife.

1157
01:36:31,586 --> 01:36:33,166
Why are you being like this?

1158
01:36:33,254 --> 01:36:36,014
You're the ace of our hotel,
and you're like a dignified crane.

1159
01:36:36,090 --> 01:36:38,470
Cranes do not hang their heads.

1160
01:36:38,551 --> 01:36:39,841
Keep your chin up!

1161
01:36:42,805 --> 01:36:46,425
I'll get the manuscript
from the publisher no matter what.

1162
01:36:47,060 --> 01:36:48,140
Mr. Koo...

1163
01:36:53,232 --> 01:36:56,612
You're refusing to return to the hotel,
so you should stay in Chan-sung's room.

1164
01:36:57,153 --> 01:36:58,783
Thank you, Mr. Koo.

1165
01:36:59,655 --> 01:37:02,905
Only the editor-in-chief has read this,
and he hasn't even finished it yet.

1166
01:37:02,992 --> 01:37:05,912
I went through hoops to persuade him
because the author is very famous.

1167
01:37:06,120 --> 01:37:07,710
How did you persuade him?

1168
01:37:07,789 --> 01:37:09,669
I told him that Kim Si-ik is my ancestor.

1169
01:37:10,416 --> 01:37:13,916
He lied that he's your descendant,
and I spent a fortune to buy it from him.

1170
01:37:14,337 --> 01:37:15,877
Thank you so much.

1171
01:37:17,048 --> 01:37:19,338
Salacious Scholar, Kim Si-ik?

1172
01:37:20,218 --> 01:37:22,508
I suppose I'll never be able
to clear my name.

1173
01:37:22,595 --> 01:37:25,095
If it's not true,
explain and prove your innocence.

1174
01:37:25,181 --> 01:37:27,771
Could you tell us what happened?

1175
01:37:30,853 --> 01:37:33,653
Everyone called me a genius
because I passed

1176
01:37:33,773 --> 01:37:35,783
the Local State Exam at a very young age.

1177
01:37:36,401 --> 01:37:39,451
However, I failed the National State Exam
every time.

1178
01:37:42,198 --> 01:37:44,278
After the age of 40,

1179
01:37:44,951 --> 01:37:47,621
I left my hometown
and settled down in Hanyang.

1180
01:37:47,703 --> 01:37:50,003
Then I focused solely
on studying for the exam.

1181
01:37:51,999 --> 01:37:54,459
While I studied alone,
whenever I felt lonely,

1182
01:37:54,710 --> 01:37:59,220
watching how others lived
was the only thing that gave me joy.

1183
01:38:00,133 --> 01:38:03,853
I saw a young girl
looking after her blind father,

1184
01:38:04,637 --> 01:38:08,267
and I also saw brothers and sisters
argue with each other all the time.

1185
01:38:08,349 --> 01:38:09,889
-My gosh.
-Hey.

1186
01:38:09,976 --> 01:38:13,306
It was beautiful
to see a young couple fall in love

1187
01:38:13,396 --> 01:38:16,066
disregarding their social status.

1188
01:38:18,109 --> 01:38:20,779
Whenever I grew bored of reading books,

1189
01:38:21,237 --> 01:38:25,657
I came up with stories
based on what I had seen on the street.

1190
01:38:26,409 --> 01:38:27,989
Master, this is so sad.

1191
01:38:28,244 --> 01:38:29,834
What happens next?

1192
01:38:32,999 --> 01:38:35,079
Of course, back then, for scholars,

1193
01:38:35,168 --> 01:38:37,958
writing a story in something else
than Chinese characters

1194
01:38:38,337 --> 01:38:40,337
was considered unconventional.

1195
01:38:40,673 --> 01:38:45,183
However, the stories I wrote
weren't vulgar at all.

1196
01:38:45,261 --> 01:38:47,221
Wait, you wrote stories

1197
01:38:47,305 --> 01:38:49,845
about a dutiful daughter,
a faithful woman, and siblings...

1198
01:38:49,932 --> 01:38:52,642
Are they about Sim Cheong,
Chun-hyang, Heung-bu, and Nol-bu?

1199
01:38:52,727 --> 01:38:54,937
You wrote all of those stories?

1200
01:38:55,062 --> 01:38:58,482
They're known to be
anonymous works to this day.

1201
01:38:59,525 --> 01:39:01,855
If that's true, you're the Shakespeare
of the Joseon Dynasty.

1202
01:39:01,944 --> 01:39:06,374
But those stories ruined my life

1203
01:39:06,991 --> 01:39:09,451
when my life was at its peak.

1204
01:39:09,785 --> 01:39:12,785
Master, congratulations.
You'll make a glorious return.

1205
01:39:13,331 --> 01:39:15,921
Your appointment will be canceled.

1206
01:39:18,961 --> 01:39:20,671
What do you mean?

1207
01:39:20,963 --> 01:39:23,223
It's my understanding
that you wrote these stories.

1208
01:39:23,716 --> 01:39:25,546
You call yourself a scholar,

1209
01:39:25,635 --> 01:39:28,135
and yet you wrote the so-called stories

1210
01:39:28,221 --> 01:39:30,721
about lowly lives of the commoners?

1211
01:39:30,806 --> 01:39:32,516
You are a disgrace to fellow scholars!

1212
01:39:32,934 --> 01:39:36,104
All the scholars will step in to make sure
that someone as vulgar and nasty as you

1213
01:39:36,187 --> 01:39:38,767
is never appointed as an official.

1214
01:39:38,981 --> 01:39:41,821
I only wrote stories about people's lives.

1215
01:39:41,901 --> 01:39:43,781
How could you call these stories vulgar?

1216
01:39:43,861 --> 01:39:46,111
A story of an adulterous couple.

1217
01:39:46,822 --> 01:39:50,122
A story where the order
between brothers is broken.

1218
01:39:50,535 --> 01:39:53,825
A story that confuses the people
through absurd imaginations.

1219
01:39:53,913 --> 01:39:57,083
How can a scholar come up
with such stories?

1220
01:39:58,543 --> 01:40:00,383
Master!

1221
01:40:04,924 --> 01:40:06,304
Kim Si-ik.

1222
01:40:07,009 --> 01:40:08,509
If you have any shame,

1223
01:40:08,594 --> 01:40:11,314
do not ever dare lift up your face again.

1224
01:40:12,890 --> 01:40:17,310
Due to the petition brought
by other scholars, I was disqualified.

1225
01:40:18,104 --> 01:40:22,364
The son of a powerful family
took my position.

1226
01:40:25,528 --> 01:40:28,108
My father who was in my hometown
was so humiliated

1227
01:40:28,698 --> 01:40:31,368
that he refused to eat and passed away.

1228
01:40:31,534 --> 01:40:35,414
I was too ashamed to face my wife
who had been supporting me.

1229
01:40:39,458 --> 01:40:42,838
As I could neither go back
to my hometown nor stay there,

1230
01:40:43,754 --> 01:40:44,764
I died

1231
01:40:46,007 --> 01:40:48,257
all by myself, feeling lost in the world.

1232
01:40:51,304 --> 01:40:53,394
I feel so wronged.

1233
01:41:04,734 --> 01:41:08,154
At first, he waited for
his so-called humiliating stories

1234
01:41:08,237 --> 01:41:10,447
to disappear in this world.

1235
01:41:10,615 --> 01:41:14,235
But people puffed up his stories,
and the stories spread even more.

1236
01:41:14,327 --> 01:41:15,537
Everyone in this world

1237
01:41:15,620 --> 01:41:18,960
knows the stories of Chun-hyang
and Sim Cheong.

1238
01:41:19,040 --> 01:41:21,040
I'm sure a part of him was
feeling hopeful.

1239
01:41:21,125 --> 01:41:24,415
He could have cleared his name
and felt proud instead.

1240
01:41:24,503 --> 01:41:27,633
However, there's no evidence.

1241
01:41:28,507 --> 01:41:31,177
Can you truly trust everything he says?

1242
01:41:33,220 --> 01:41:35,640
No wonder
someone would write a book about him.

1243
01:41:35,765 --> 01:41:37,765
People don't know
about the stories he wrote.

1244
01:41:37,850 --> 01:41:39,690
He just became a salacious scholar

1245
01:41:39,769 --> 01:41:41,769
who got disqualified in the end

1246
01:41:42,188 --> 01:41:44,108
because of his so-called vulgar stories.

1247
01:41:46,192 --> 01:41:48,782
I will read every page of this manuscript.

1248
01:41:49,028 --> 01:41:51,738
Mr. Kim is okay though, right?

1249
01:41:51,822 --> 01:41:54,372
He will stay in my room for now.

1250
01:41:57,662 --> 01:41:58,792
Sanchez.

1251
01:42:03,668 --> 01:42:06,708
I remember seeing you
at the dinner the other day.

1252
01:42:07,922 --> 01:42:10,092
Yes. What brings you here?

1253
01:42:10,174 --> 01:42:11,384
I have a situation,

1254
01:42:11,467 --> 01:42:13,927
so I'll be staying
in Mr. Koo's room for a while.

1255
01:42:14,011 --> 01:42:15,301
I see.

1256
01:42:15,638 --> 01:42:18,718
Then does he also work at the hotel?

1257
01:42:20,226 --> 01:42:21,346
He's the Grim Reaper.

1258
01:42:23,896 --> 01:42:26,816
He's not an easy man to meet
when you're alive.

1259
01:42:27,024 --> 01:42:28,114
Say hello.

1260
01:42:31,821 --> 01:42:35,411
But he's not here
because he has business with me, right?

1261
01:42:35,491 --> 01:42:38,701
No. I'm here to console
an old friend of mine.

1262
01:42:46,419 --> 01:42:48,169
The Grim Reaper bought me some beer.

1263
01:42:48,254 --> 01:42:49,884
Would you like to join us?

1264
01:42:49,964 --> 01:42:51,884
No, I'm good. Please go ahead.

1265
01:42:52,049 --> 01:42:53,719
Please allow me to stay for a while.

1266
01:42:53,801 --> 01:42:54,801
Sure.

1267
01:42:55,261 --> 01:42:56,641
-Hey.
-Yes?

1268
01:42:57,930 --> 01:43:00,640
As I didn't have any food for beer,
I picked some jujube in your yard.

1269
01:43:00,725 --> 01:43:02,225
If we meet in the future,

1270
01:43:03,269 --> 01:43:05,229
I'll repay you for them.

1271
01:43:09,024 --> 01:43:10,074
Sure.

1272
01:43:10,901 --> 01:43:13,951
I have peanuts. Do you want me
to bring some peanuts?

1273
01:43:14,029 --> 01:43:15,239
Excuse me.

1274
01:43:18,033 --> 01:43:21,043
I didn't know
that's what had happened to Kim Si-ik.

1275
01:43:21,370 --> 01:43:22,910
It's unfortunate,

1276
01:43:23,080 --> 01:43:25,250
but I don't want to go
against 500-year-old grudges

1277
01:43:25,332 --> 01:43:27,252
to publish the book.

1278
01:43:27,793 --> 01:43:28,793
I will get rid of it.

1279
01:43:29,837 --> 01:43:32,007
It would be a shame
to destroy it like this.

1280
01:43:32,173 --> 01:43:34,433
My manager read every page of the novel.

1281
01:43:34,508 --> 01:43:36,508
He told me the story was
quite fascinating.

1282
01:43:36,969 --> 01:43:40,509
If I were to overlook
the perverted scholar part,

1283
01:43:40,598 --> 01:43:44,558
the scholar character is quite enticing
and fascinating, from what I heard.

1284
01:43:44,643 --> 01:43:47,403
He's a noble-minded scholar
who doesn't get involved

1285
01:43:47,480 --> 01:43:49,110
in the conflict
between two major factions.

1286
01:43:49,190 --> 01:43:53,240
He's also a romantic scholar,
who writes to his wife once a month

1287
01:43:53,319 --> 01:43:55,359
while she waits for him at this hometown.

1288
01:43:55,488 --> 01:43:58,158
I did my research.
That's what Kim Si-ik did.

1289
01:43:58,240 --> 01:44:00,620
I'll tell you what. "Kim Si-ik decided

1290
01:44:00,701 --> 01:44:02,911
not to join the social cliques
to gain power.

1291
01:44:02,995 --> 01:44:03,995
As an outsider,

1292
01:44:04,079 --> 01:44:06,999
he indulged himself
in perverted, erotic stories."

1293
01:44:07,208 --> 01:44:09,338
Let's just change this part.

1294
01:44:09,794 --> 01:44:13,094
"The existing stories, written
in the Korean alphabet by unknown writers,

1295
01:44:13,672 --> 01:44:15,672
were actually written
by the scholar, Kim Si-ik."

1296
01:44:15,841 --> 01:44:18,261
You won't be able to write this
in a historical book,

1297
01:44:18,344 --> 01:44:20,934
but it would make
a very fascinating theme for a novel.

1298
01:44:21,013 --> 01:44:22,313
You're right.

1299
01:44:22,556 --> 01:44:24,766
"Shin Yun-bok was a woman."

1300
01:44:24,850 --> 01:44:26,390
There's a book with that theme too.

1301
01:44:26,685 --> 01:44:28,805
In novels, everything is possible.

1302
01:44:28,896 --> 01:44:30,016
Let's go with that then.

1303
01:44:30,105 --> 01:44:32,145
The most romantic scholar
and the best storyteller

1304
01:44:32,233 --> 01:44:34,613
in the Joseon Dynasty,
who was as noble as a crane.

1305
01:44:34,693 --> 01:44:35,743
Kim Si-ik.

1306
01:44:36,821 --> 01:44:40,281
"Crane"? This title just crossed my mind.

1307
01:44:40,658 --> 01:44:43,408
My masterpiece, The War of Cranes,

1308
01:44:43,494 --> 01:44:46,754
is followed by this beautiful novel
called A Song of a Crane.

1309
01:44:48,833 --> 01:44:51,843
A Song of a Crane. Let's sing that song.

1310
01:44:58,259 --> 01:45:00,839
Sir, write a great story.

1311
01:45:10,187 --> 01:45:11,227
What just happened?

1312
01:45:11,522 --> 01:45:13,362
A Song of a Crane!

1313
01:45:13,607 --> 01:45:15,687
You must start the song.
What are you doing?

1314
01:45:15,776 --> 01:45:18,446
This happens all the time to people
who died from overwork.

1315
01:45:18,529 --> 01:45:22,029
I forgot to mention
that he passes out within 30 seconds

1316
01:45:22,658 --> 01:45:24,078
upon grabbing his pen.

1317
01:45:24,368 --> 01:45:26,498
What? If he keeps passing out

1318
01:45:26,579 --> 01:45:27,749
every 30 seconds,

1319
01:45:27,830 --> 01:45:29,500
when will he finish his novel?

1320
01:45:30,791 --> 01:45:32,501
We must get help from another writer.

1321
01:45:33,043 --> 01:45:35,303
What? Another writer? Who?

1322
01:45:35,796 --> 01:45:39,586
We have a novelist
who wanted to work hard, but couldn't

1323
01:45:39,675 --> 01:45:41,215
before he died.

1324
01:45:42,595 --> 01:45:44,805
Sir, from what I've observed so far,

1325
01:45:44,888 --> 01:45:48,098
your writing is superb.

1326
01:45:48,309 --> 01:45:50,229
But you haven't decided

1327
01:45:50,311 --> 01:45:53,691
what to write about yet.

1328
01:45:54,106 --> 01:45:56,936
We have a great topic
as well as an excellent teacher.

1329
01:45:57,026 --> 01:45:58,276
Will you

1330
01:45:59,028 --> 01:46:00,608
complete a novel?

1331
01:46:04,366 --> 01:46:08,536
Does that mean I'll remain
as a character in a fictional story?

1332
01:46:08,621 --> 01:46:10,581
Kim Si-ik is recorded as a scholar

1333
01:46:10,664 --> 01:46:14,044
who got disqualified
for writing vulgar stories.

1334
01:46:14,543 --> 01:46:15,883
There's only one line.

1335
01:46:17,129 --> 01:46:20,339
That will not disappear
even if you wait for 500 years.

1336
01:46:21,050 --> 01:46:22,130
Is that so?

1337
01:46:24,053 --> 01:46:25,553
But it's not fictional

1338
01:46:25,638 --> 01:46:28,308
that you were an affectionate husband
and noble scholar.

1339
01:46:28,390 --> 01:46:30,890
Remaining in this world in a novel

1340
01:46:31,185 --> 01:46:33,145
seems good enough to me.

1341
01:46:33,228 --> 01:46:34,608
Is that so?

1342
01:46:35,522 --> 01:46:37,902
Besides, it's a novel.

1343
01:46:37,983 --> 01:46:40,943
While we're at it,
let's say that he was tall

1344
01:46:41,028 --> 01:46:42,948
and very handsome.

1345
01:46:43,030 --> 01:46:44,320
How will they know?

1346
01:46:44,406 --> 01:46:47,156
Is there anyone you think you resemble?

1347
01:46:47,242 --> 01:46:48,582
There's a guy

1348
01:46:48,661 --> 01:46:51,831
who I think resembles me a lot.

1349
01:46:51,914 --> 01:46:53,374
Okay. Who is it?

1350
01:46:54,166 --> 01:46:58,126
Young people call him Mr. Hip.

1351
01:46:59,088 --> 01:47:00,298
So Ji-sub?

1352
01:47:01,131 --> 01:47:03,471
Are you telling me
that you resemble So Ji-sub?

1353
01:47:03,717 --> 01:47:05,297
Come on, you...

1354
01:47:07,846 --> 01:47:10,636
You definitely look like him!

1355
01:47:10,724 --> 01:47:12,394
Yes. You look just like him.

1356
01:47:12,476 --> 01:47:14,136
I resemble him even more from this side.

1357
01:47:14,228 --> 01:47:15,898
Goodness, you're right.

1358
01:47:15,979 --> 01:47:17,309
Turn around a bit more.

1359
01:47:17,398 --> 01:47:19,858
Keep turning.

1360
01:47:19,942 --> 01:47:21,192
Yes, that's it.

1361
01:47:21,276 --> 01:47:24,906
The back of your head
is pitch black just like his.

1362
01:47:25,406 --> 01:47:27,566
Goodness, Mr. Kim.

1363
01:47:27,658 --> 01:47:30,368
You're a hip, handsome guy.

1364
01:47:50,681 --> 01:47:53,311
Kim Si-ik can even do martial arts.

1365
01:47:53,392 --> 01:47:54,772
He sounds pretty cool.

1366
01:47:56,228 --> 01:47:59,358
Gosh, the writer romanticized
the guy too much.

1367
01:47:59,732 --> 01:48:00,942
This will be a hit.

1368
01:48:02,484 --> 01:48:04,784
Ms. Jang. Mr. Koo.

1369
01:48:05,028 --> 01:48:06,658
The last part is complete.

1370
01:48:07,281 --> 01:48:08,821
Let's see.

1371
01:48:17,958 --> 01:48:19,128
It's good.

1372
01:48:23,380 --> 01:48:24,630
Mr. Kim.

1373
01:48:25,382 --> 01:48:29,552
There's a draft of a book
I received from a rookie writer.

1374
01:48:29,678 --> 01:48:33,178
Check the second shelf
of the bookcase in my writing room.

1375
01:48:34,099 --> 01:48:38,599
The story is about a scholar,
Kim Si-ik in the Joseon Dynasty,

1376
01:48:39,146 --> 01:48:42,686
and the author's name is Bae Seong-hun.

1377
01:48:43,817 --> 01:48:46,237
Yes, of course.

1378
01:48:47,362 --> 01:48:48,362
Right.

1379
01:48:48,447 --> 01:48:53,157
A SONG OF A CRANE

1380
01:49:10,761 --> 01:49:12,261
The book has been published,

1381
01:49:12,554 --> 01:49:15,434
and our two writers left
with smiles on their faces.

1382
01:49:15,682 --> 01:49:19,352
I made these cocktails
as a token of my gratitude,

1383
01:49:19,895 --> 01:49:20,975
so please enjoy them.

1384
01:49:30,572 --> 01:49:32,832
I said I'm not a fan of Tears.

1385
01:49:32,991 --> 01:49:35,791
Still, it's for a special occasion
this time,

1386
01:49:35,869 --> 01:49:37,289
so please drink up.

1387
01:49:37,830 --> 01:49:40,290
What's the meaning behind it this time?

1388
01:49:42,459 --> 01:49:44,039
They are tears of a sad goodbye.

1389
01:49:53,971 --> 01:49:58,891
I, Kim Si-ik, a scholar of Joseon,
have washed away my shame.

1390
01:49:59,268 --> 01:50:02,688
With these tears that symbolize
my reluctance to leave,

1391
01:50:03,814 --> 01:50:05,484
I will now head to the afterlife.

1392
01:50:08,193 --> 01:50:09,573
Mr. Kim...

1393
01:50:10,904 --> 01:50:12,114
We will

1394
01:50:13,448 --> 01:50:15,448
gulp down our tears with this drink...

1395
01:50:17,870 --> 01:50:19,000
and say goodbye.

1396
01:50:24,501 --> 01:50:26,921
Thank you for everything.

1397
01:50:48,859 --> 01:50:51,699
I thank you for all your hard work
and apologize for leaving first.

1398
01:50:56,325 --> 01:50:58,155
Take care, Mr. Kim.

1399
01:51:09,004 --> 01:51:12,554
It's been 70 years,
but you're still like a baby.

1400
01:51:24,311 --> 01:51:25,651
Goodbye, Mr. Kim.

1401
01:51:43,705 --> 01:51:44,865
I'll get going.

1402
01:52:09,314 --> 01:52:13,244
THE SAMDO RIVER
THIS LIFE, THE AFTERLIFE

1403
01:52:18,824 --> 01:52:20,244
Goodbye.

1404
01:52:46,977 --> 01:52:48,187
Ms. Jang.

1405
01:52:48,895 --> 01:52:51,185
Thank you for preserving my name

1406
01:52:51,523 --> 01:52:55,243
and letting me be remembered
as a scholar as mysterious as a crane.

1407
01:52:56,278 --> 01:52:59,738
These are the tears
I give to you as my gratitude.

1408
01:53:00,157 --> 01:53:02,577
I hope that the cold and icy moon of yours

1409
01:53:03,076 --> 01:53:05,786
will go down

1410
01:53:06,038 --> 01:53:08,248
beautifully and warmly.

1411
01:53:30,604 --> 01:53:32,314
This tastes awful.

1412
01:54:21,196 --> 01:54:22,856
Why don't you come
to the hotel these days?

1413
01:54:24,491 --> 01:54:26,491
Why would I when it'll soon be gone?

1414
01:54:27,577 --> 01:54:29,157
I came to check if Hyeon-mi had died

1415
01:54:29,246 --> 01:54:32,416
because that would mean
you'd soon be leaving too.

1416
01:54:33,792 --> 01:54:36,712
Well, Mr. Kim left.

1417
01:54:40,882 --> 01:54:44,262
See? You're sad because he left too.

1418
01:54:44,636 --> 01:54:47,096
That's how I'll feel if you go.

1419
01:54:47,347 --> 01:54:49,467
Please say that you'll stay.

1420
01:54:51,017 --> 01:54:52,437
It's sad

1421
01:54:53,353 --> 01:54:54,863
that he's no longer with us,

1422
01:54:55,605 --> 01:54:59,525
but we sent him off with joy.

1423
01:55:02,654 --> 01:55:04,534
Because nothing is sadder

1424
01:55:05,323 --> 01:55:06,993
than staying in this world.

1425
01:55:07,075 --> 01:55:10,035
What's sad about being with me?

1426
01:55:10,120 --> 01:55:11,830
Look at me and my sister.

1427
01:55:12,539 --> 01:55:15,579
Is that what you want for us?

1428
01:55:26,219 --> 01:55:27,429
Fine, leave then.

1429
01:55:27,637 --> 01:55:29,847
But I can't stay and watch you leave.

1430
01:55:30,140 --> 01:55:32,770
Kim Yu-na's parents keep telling me
to go and study abroad.

1431
01:55:33,101 --> 01:55:35,941
I think I'll just go. It's perfect, right?

1432
01:55:36,980 --> 01:55:38,610
You can go to the afterlife,

1433
01:55:39,274 --> 01:55:40,694
and I'll go abroad.

1434
01:55:40,817 --> 01:55:42,937
Let's just leave our graves behind here...

1435
01:55:44,821 --> 01:55:46,031
and say our farewell.

1436
01:56:16,394 --> 01:56:17,604
Thank you.

1437
01:56:19,981 --> 01:56:21,151
Excuse me.

1438
01:56:26,530 --> 01:56:29,620
I've seen you
watching from outside the pharmacy.

1439
01:56:29,950 --> 01:56:33,120
Are you perhaps a relative
of my baby's father?

1440
01:56:34,621 --> 01:56:36,291
I was once

1441
01:56:36,456 --> 01:56:39,126
a daughter-in-law of
the Yeongju Yun family.

1442
01:56:44,297 --> 01:56:46,507
My baby will never be

1443
01:56:46,633 --> 01:56:48,553
of the Yeongju Yun family.

1444
01:56:48,885 --> 01:56:50,635
It will take my surname instead.

1445
01:56:52,222 --> 01:56:53,392
If it's a son,

1446
01:56:53,807 --> 01:56:56,977
he'll be the sole heir
who'll carry on the family line.

1447
01:56:57,435 --> 01:57:00,435
And a daughter will equally
be the sole heir too.

1448
01:57:00,522 --> 01:57:02,152
They don't carry on
the family line though.

1449
01:57:02,232 --> 01:57:04,942
Once she marries, she'll become a member

1450
01:57:05,026 --> 01:57:06,606
of her husband's family and--

1451
01:57:06,695 --> 01:57:08,565
Are you from Joseon or something?

1452
01:57:08,738 --> 01:57:10,948
No one thinks like that
in this day and age.

1453
01:57:11,199 --> 01:57:14,239
If the grandparents want to see my baby,

1454
01:57:14,327 --> 01:57:15,577
then I'll let them.

1455
01:57:15,662 --> 01:57:18,962
But, whether it's a boy or a girl,

1456
01:57:19,040 --> 01:57:21,130
this baby will just be

1457
01:57:21,585 --> 01:57:23,035
my child.

1458
01:57:45,942 --> 01:57:47,192
What's wrong?

1459
01:57:47,861 --> 01:57:49,281
Why...

1460
01:57:50,322 --> 01:57:52,242
did I never think of that

1461
01:57:53,033 --> 01:57:55,243
for my daughter?

1462
01:57:56,745 --> 01:57:58,325
I feel so sorry for her.

1463
01:58:07,005 --> 01:58:08,545
This child...

1464
01:58:09,674 --> 01:58:13,434
I just hope the child inside your womb

1465
01:58:13,887 --> 01:58:15,757
will be born healthy,

1466
01:58:16,848 --> 01:58:18,928
and live a good life.

1467
01:58:28,485 --> 01:58:29,855
THE GUYS WHO DIED AFTER EATING

1468
01:58:33,531 --> 01:58:34,741
Look.

1469
01:58:35,075 --> 01:58:36,075
This.

1470
01:58:37,285 --> 01:58:39,155
And this one. Which one should I post?

1471
01:58:39,245 --> 01:58:40,285
This one is good.

1472
01:58:40,372 --> 01:58:42,042
This one? Okay.

1473
01:58:43,249 --> 01:58:45,959
You take so many photos.
Do you have any followers?

1474
01:58:46,044 --> 01:58:49,304
Of course. Hyeon-jung, Yu-na, and Sanchez.

1475
01:58:50,048 --> 01:58:50,968
That's all?

1476
01:58:51,549 --> 01:58:54,049
Your boiled egg looks much better.

1477
01:58:55,220 --> 01:58:56,890
You were taking so many pictures.

1478
01:58:56,971 --> 01:58:59,351
I thought you had
about a million followers.

1479
01:58:59,432 --> 01:59:03,142
You haven't even pressed "like" once.
You have no right to say that.

1480
01:59:03,520 --> 01:59:04,810
I don't do social media.

1481
01:59:04,896 --> 01:59:07,646
-Alex Ferguson once said--
-Forget it.

1482
01:59:07,857 --> 01:59:11,067
I'm sure he said something great.

1483
01:59:11,152 --> 01:59:14,202
But that's what he thinks. I will...

1484
01:59:18,326 --> 01:59:19,736
What is it now?

1485
01:59:21,621 --> 01:59:22,711
Like...

1486
01:59:23,873 --> 01:59:26,253
He pressed "like."

1487
01:59:26,793 --> 01:59:29,253
Who? Sanchez?

1488
01:59:30,714 --> 01:59:33,474
Kim Jun-hyun...

1489
01:59:34,718 --> 01:59:36,178
Kim Jun-hyun did.

1490
01:59:37,220 --> 01:59:40,180
Look at this. He pressed "like"
for the picture I posted

1491
01:59:40,598 --> 01:59:42,058
about the rice with thistle.

1492
01:59:43,143 --> 01:59:45,403
LIKE
KIM JUN-HYUN

1493
01:59:45,562 --> 01:59:46,902
He really did.

1494
01:59:47,731 --> 01:59:49,191
You only have three followers.

1495
01:59:49,274 --> 01:59:51,694
How did he find your post
and press "like"?

1496
01:59:51,776 --> 01:59:54,946
I don't wish for anything more.

1497
01:59:55,029 --> 01:59:57,819
I have been recognized
by the master gourmet.

1498
01:59:59,367 --> 02:00:03,077
Since when did you like
Kim Jun-hyun so much?

1499
02:00:03,163 --> 02:00:04,163
What?

1500
02:00:08,793 --> 02:00:11,053
From the first time I saw him,

1501
02:00:11,129 --> 02:00:12,839
I knew he's my cup of tea.

1502
02:00:12,922 --> 02:00:15,632
He looks like someone I know.

1503
02:00:16,176 --> 02:00:19,596
I was going through hard times
because of my undesirable hobby.

1504
02:00:19,679 --> 02:00:22,679
Suddenly a young guy appeared
and saved me with the game of Go.

1505
02:00:22,766 --> 02:00:25,636
He also recommended
I go on a gourmet tour.

1506
02:00:26,060 --> 02:00:29,610
He looks exactly like Kim Jun-hyun.

1507
02:00:30,815 --> 02:00:31,975
But that's me.

1508
02:00:32,859 --> 02:00:33,779
What?

1509
02:00:33,860 --> 02:00:36,070
I told you I went
to Man-wol Inn 200 years ago

1510
02:00:36,154 --> 02:00:37,324
to get the Moon flowers.

1511
02:00:37,405 --> 02:00:40,275
It was me who won the game of Go
and drew you the gourmet map.

1512
02:00:40,825 --> 02:00:41,785
It was me.

1513
02:00:41,868 --> 02:00:43,238
Don't be ridiculous.

1514
02:00:43,328 --> 02:00:46,708
I remember clearly.
He had a big build like Kim Jun-hyun.

1515
02:00:46,790 --> 02:00:49,130
He was very nice and kind.

1516
02:00:49,918 --> 02:00:52,878
You wouldn't even be one-fourth of
the man he is, no matter how hard you try.

1517
02:00:53,046 --> 02:00:54,376
What are you trying to do?

1518
02:00:58,718 --> 02:01:01,178
That's the way Mago changed your memories.

1519
02:01:04,390 --> 02:01:08,850
Now I realize that we did visit
so many good restaurants.

1520
02:01:11,773 --> 02:01:13,023
They were all good.

1521
02:01:19,614 --> 02:01:23,374
Lastly, there is something
you have to eat.

1522
02:01:51,271 --> 02:01:52,401
You have to

1523
02:01:53,147 --> 02:01:54,817
eat that later.

1524
02:01:58,987 --> 02:02:00,027
You have to.

1525
02:02:05,743 --> 02:02:07,833
Let's eat. Naengmyeon is getting cold.

1526
02:02:11,416 --> 02:02:13,666
Okay. Let's eat before it gets cold.

1527
02:02:18,423 --> 02:02:19,593
Do you want mustard?

1528
02:02:20,425 --> 02:02:23,425
Kim Jun-hyun said you need vinegar
when you have Pyongyang naengmyeon.

1529
02:02:25,179 --> 02:02:26,469
Wasn't that Baek Jong-won?

1530
02:02:27,682 --> 02:02:28,602
It could be.

1531
02:02:28,683 --> 02:02:30,773
You're 1,300 years old for sure.

1532
02:02:30,852 --> 02:02:32,772
You are confused about
what your favorite guy said.

1533
02:02:33,438 --> 02:02:35,188
-How much?
-Just a little.

1534
02:02:39,068 --> 02:02:40,648
It looks delicious.

1535
02:02:41,613 --> 02:02:42,913
Aren't you adding any?

1536
02:02:43,615 --> 02:02:46,275
With Pyongyang naengmyeon,
you have to taste the broth first.

1537
02:03:05,219 --> 02:03:07,759
Of all the room service staff,
you will be the only one left.

1538
02:03:08,139 --> 02:03:10,599
Most of the guests are gone too.

1539
02:03:11,225 --> 02:03:12,975
Thanks for all your work.

1540
02:03:15,313 --> 02:03:16,813
-We will be going.
-Okay.

1541
02:03:20,693 --> 02:03:21,953
Ms. Choe.

1542
02:03:25,865 --> 02:03:26,905
Yes.

1543
02:03:29,786 --> 02:03:32,326
I have to go to get Hyeon-mi.

1544
02:03:32,997 --> 02:03:34,787
Tae-seok contacted me.

1545
02:03:38,211 --> 02:03:39,801
Bring your sister here.

1546
02:03:40,421 --> 02:03:42,171
I'll let Ms. Jang know.

1547
02:04:05,405 --> 02:04:08,565
Hyeon-mi, I am here.

1548
02:04:09,409 --> 02:04:10,949
Hyeon-jung.

1549
02:04:25,633 --> 02:04:26,883
Hyeon-mi.

1550
02:04:27,176 --> 02:04:28,586
Hyeon-jung.

1551
02:04:38,521 --> 02:04:41,021
Do you know how long I've waited for you?

1552
02:04:45,611 --> 02:04:46,611
Let's go.

1553
02:05:05,465 --> 02:05:06,505
Yu-na.

1554
02:05:43,294 --> 02:05:46,094
You must be Hyeon-jung's sister, Hyeon-mi.

1555
02:05:46,255 --> 02:05:50,085
Thanks to your kind brother,
you'll leave without losing your way.

1556
02:05:51,886 --> 02:05:52,886
What about Yu-na?

1557
02:05:53,721 --> 02:05:56,221
Does she know you are leaving?

1558
02:05:56,557 --> 02:05:58,807
I saw her at the hospital.

1559
02:06:08,194 --> 02:06:10,494
Could you give this to her for me?

1560
02:06:15,368 --> 02:06:16,408
And...

1561
02:06:17,245 --> 02:06:18,325
Please tell her

1562
02:06:18,788 --> 02:06:22,128
that every single second she has left

1563
02:06:22,667 --> 02:06:24,747
is all so precious,

1564
02:06:25,586 --> 02:06:27,546
so she should be a good student

1565
02:06:28,798 --> 02:06:30,088
and be happy.

1566
02:07:01,914 --> 02:07:03,084
Ma'am.

1567
02:07:06,627 --> 02:07:07,797
Ma'am.

1568
02:07:08,129 --> 02:07:11,009
I'd be happy to give
all the time I have left.

1569
02:07:11,465 --> 02:07:13,215
Please grant me a favor.

1570
02:07:34,906 --> 02:07:36,156
Hyeon-jung.

1571
02:07:53,466 --> 02:07:54,876
Take them with you.

1572
02:07:58,554 --> 02:08:00,934
You left flowers on my grave too.

1573
02:08:02,141 --> 02:08:04,271
I got these for you.

1574
02:08:04,977 --> 02:08:06,937
I asked Mago

1575
02:08:07,146 --> 02:08:09,726
and I put myself in huge debt
to get them for you.

1576
02:08:10,775 --> 02:08:12,855
She told me that I have to live
a really good life

1577
02:08:12,944 --> 02:08:16,284
in order to repay her
for the favor she's done for me.

1578
02:08:16,989 --> 02:08:19,489
So you don't need to worry about me.

1579
02:08:22,787 --> 02:08:23,957
Thank you.

1580
02:08:27,041 --> 02:08:28,381
I won't worry.

1581
02:08:38,427 --> 02:08:40,847
Bye, Hyeon-jung.

1582
02:08:44,141 --> 02:08:45,311
Goodbye.

1583
02:09:28,477 --> 02:09:32,647
Why are you suddenly meeting Mi-ra's
parents? Are you planning to marry?

1584
02:09:33,149 --> 02:09:34,189
We're

1585
02:09:34,859 --> 02:09:36,739
going to get married this winter.

1586
02:09:39,363 --> 02:09:41,453
Then that's going to be
a really important event.

1587
02:09:41,532 --> 02:09:45,162
It's weird that you'd want to meet
her parents at a pizza restaurant.

1588
02:09:45,411 --> 02:09:46,951
We chose this place because of you.

1589
02:09:47,329 --> 02:09:50,169
You have no idea
how much my parents trust you.

1590
02:09:50,249 --> 02:09:51,999
Back when they came
to the States to take me back,

1591
02:09:52,084 --> 02:09:53,884
all of my friends helped me hide
from them,

1592
02:09:53,961 --> 02:09:55,421
but you told them where I was.

1593
02:09:55,504 --> 02:09:57,474
You scored
a lot of brownie points with them.

1594
02:09:57,548 --> 02:09:59,338
They think you're a very honest friend.

1595
02:09:59,425 --> 02:10:03,885
Well, it's nice to hear
that your parents think I'm trustworthy.

1596
02:10:03,971 --> 02:10:06,181
But I still don't get
why you'd want me to be here

1597
02:10:06,265 --> 02:10:07,975
when you introduce him to your parents.

1598
02:10:08,059 --> 02:10:11,399
If my parents end up not liking Yeong-su,

1599
02:10:11,479 --> 02:10:13,059
you should help me convince them.

1600
02:10:13,147 --> 02:10:16,527
Why? It's your marriage.
And I'm not even his brother.

1601
02:10:16,817 --> 02:10:19,527
I don't have a family to introduce her to,

1602
02:10:19,737 --> 02:10:21,407
so she must be really worried.

1603
02:10:21,989 --> 02:10:24,409
Sanchez, can you be his older brother?

1604
02:10:24,700 --> 02:10:26,740
You should tell them
what a great guy Yeong-su is.

1605
02:10:26,827 --> 02:10:28,157
You know what I mean, right?

1606
02:10:28,245 --> 02:10:30,495
Actually, just tell them
that I'm pregnant.

1607
02:10:31,248 --> 02:10:34,668
I'm not a gynecologist.
I'm just an owner of a pizza restaurant.

1608
02:10:34,752 --> 02:10:36,592
You're being really weird.

1609
02:10:37,171 --> 02:10:41,221
Mi-ra, you shouldn't lie
to your parents like that.

1610
02:10:41,300 --> 02:10:42,970
If they happen to disapprove of me,

1611
02:10:43,427 --> 02:10:45,217
I'll do my best to convince them.

1612
02:10:45,304 --> 02:10:48,684
I just don't want you to feel lonely.

1613
02:10:49,642 --> 02:10:51,392
I can't wait to become your family.

1614
02:10:52,353 --> 02:10:53,483
Mi-ra.

1615
02:11:01,946 --> 02:11:04,776
I guess they won't have any problems
getting married this winter.

1616
02:11:09,620 --> 02:11:12,370
We're so different when it comes
to choosing a refrigerator.

1617
02:11:12,456 --> 02:11:14,496
It's better to have a bigger freezer.

1618
02:11:14,583 --> 02:11:17,133
There are so many things
to store in the freezer.

1619
02:11:17,211 --> 02:11:19,551
You never eat anything
from the freezer anyway.

1620
02:11:19,630 --> 02:11:21,970
Let's just buy one
that has a big refrigerating space

1621
02:11:22,049 --> 02:11:23,299
so we can eat fresh food.

1622
02:11:24,510 --> 02:11:25,510
Honey.

1623
02:11:26,804 --> 02:11:28,474
Do you choose me
or the refrigerating space?

1624
02:11:29,014 --> 02:11:32,314
Your love for me should be equal
to the size of the freezer.

1625
02:11:33,727 --> 02:11:35,597
I love you as much as the size
of the North Pole.

1626
02:11:35,688 --> 02:11:38,518
So let's get a fridge
that has a lot of refrigerating space.

1627
02:11:38,774 --> 02:11:39,614
Done.

1628
02:11:39,692 --> 02:11:42,032
Forget it. I'm going to go
take a look at the furniture.

1629
02:11:50,411 --> 02:11:51,751
Stop right there.

1630
02:11:54,165 --> 02:11:55,245
Ms. Jang?

1631
02:11:55,624 --> 02:11:57,004
You're getting married,

1632
02:11:57,418 --> 02:11:58,338
Ms. Lee?

1633
02:11:59,170 --> 02:12:00,750
Did Chan-sung tell you?

1634
02:12:00,838 --> 02:12:02,838
Where is he? Is he here with you?

1635
02:12:02,923 --> 02:12:04,553
He went to get some milk tea,

1636
02:12:04,967 --> 02:12:05,967
Ms. Lee.

1637
02:12:07,011 --> 02:12:08,851
I asked if you're getting married.

1638
02:12:10,306 --> 02:12:12,806
Yes, we're getting married this winter.

1639
02:12:13,517 --> 02:12:15,637
I'll give you an invitation
once we finish printing them.

1640
02:12:15,728 --> 02:12:17,808
I'd like to give you a gift first.

1641
02:12:18,355 --> 02:12:19,315
A gift for me?

1642
02:12:19,398 --> 02:12:21,978
I wanted to give you

1643
02:12:22,526 --> 02:12:24,026
an unforgettable gift.

1644
02:12:25,362 --> 02:12:26,362
Look.

1645
02:12:37,708 --> 02:12:38,828
Song-hwa.

1646
02:12:42,087 --> 02:12:43,127
Song-hwa.

1647
02:12:44,131 --> 02:12:45,761
You better be good to Yeon-u.

1648
02:12:47,218 --> 02:12:49,428
If you ever make him cry,

1649
02:12:49,678 --> 02:12:52,428
I'll turn your life upside down
just like that TV.

1650
02:12:59,647 --> 02:13:00,937
Do you like it?

1651
02:13:04,151 --> 02:13:05,151
Yes.

1652
02:13:05,236 --> 02:13:07,776
I'll get you this TV as a wedding gift.

1653
02:13:07,863 --> 02:13:09,453
I hope whenever you look at it,

1654
02:13:09,531 --> 02:13:12,791
you'll always remember what I just said.

1655
02:13:20,960 --> 02:13:22,460
What did you say to Mi-ra?

1656
02:13:23,212 --> 02:13:24,212
I just said I hoped

1657
02:13:24,296 --> 02:13:26,916
they'll have a happy life
as they watch TV together.

1658
02:13:33,931 --> 02:13:35,721
You gave Mi-ra a wedding gift?

1659
02:13:35,808 --> 02:13:36,808
Yes.

1660
02:13:37,559 --> 02:13:39,399
I heard they're getting married in winter.

1661
02:13:39,770 --> 02:13:41,650
I won't be able to buy them
anything in winter

1662
02:13:42,690 --> 02:13:44,400
since I won't be here anymore.

1663
02:13:54,785 --> 02:13:56,785
Ms. Choe's leaving today.

1664
02:14:04,837 --> 02:14:06,297
The full moon will be here soon.

1665
02:14:10,843 --> 02:14:12,803
Your Guest House of the Moon

1666
02:14:13,512 --> 02:14:14,932
will only exist

1667
02:14:16,056 --> 02:14:17,926
up until the next full moon.

1668
02:14:24,273 --> 02:14:25,863
Your hands are cold.

1669
02:14:26,734 --> 02:14:28,324
Should I get you a warm drink?

1670
02:14:28,610 --> 02:14:29,610
No.

1671
02:14:30,195 --> 02:14:31,855
It's nice. It feels like winter.

1672
02:14:32,906 --> 02:14:35,196
But why did you get her a TV?

1673
02:14:35,284 --> 02:14:37,754
I noticed
that the TV could flip upside down.

1674
02:14:38,579 --> 02:14:39,579
What about that?

1675
02:14:40,080 --> 02:14:41,330
You don't need to know.

1676
02:14:42,666 --> 02:14:43,666
You remember

1677
02:14:44,335 --> 02:14:45,625
Yeon-u, right?

1678
02:14:46,003 --> 02:14:47,713
Who's Yeon-u?

1679
02:14:48,797 --> 02:14:52,217
He's no longer the person
who loves you the most.

1680
02:14:55,262 --> 02:14:56,352
I know.

1681
02:14:57,598 --> 02:14:58,928
It's Ms. Choe now.

1682
02:15:19,787 --> 02:15:20,907
The rooms

1683
02:15:21,789 --> 02:15:23,749
are all empty now.

1684
02:15:47,439 --> 02:15:50,399
Ms. Jang, I'll be off now.

1685
02:15:51,610 --> 02:15:54,700
Thank you for letting me stay here
all these years

1686
02:15:55,906 --> 02:15:57,116
and protecting me.

1687
02:15:58,200 --> 02:15:59,870
Thanks to you,

1688
02:16:01,245 --> 02:16:03,205
I was able to learn a big lesson

1689
02:16:03,956 --> 02:16:05,666
at a very important moment.

1690
02:16:08,335 --> 02:16:09,455
Thank you.

1691
02:16:15,843 --> 02:16:17,263
Mr. Koo.

1692
02:16:18,387 --> 02:16:21,887
I was the one who suggested
that we should make you enter Room 13.

1693
02:16:22,683 --> 02:16:25,063
I've been feeling guilty about that.

1694
02:16:26,311 --> 02:16:27,561
I'm sorry.

1695
02:16:28,063 --> 02:16:29,443
It's okay.

1696
02:16:31,066 --> 02:16:33,066
If I didn't enter Room 13 that day,

1697
02:16:33,694 --> 02:16:35,864
I wouldn't have been able
to obtain that one second.

1698
02:16:35,946 --> 02:16:38,196
Even if you ever get to obtain
an entire lifetime,

1699
02:16:38,282 --> 02:16:41,032
don't ever let anyone see you
wearing your tiger print suit.

1700
02:16:41,118 --> 02:16:42,908
It'll make you lose everything.

1701
02:16:44,204 --> 02:16:45,504
I'll keep that in mind.

1702
02:16:46,707 --> 02:16:47,827
Ms. Jang.

1703
02:16:48,959 --> 02:16:50,589
Now that we're about to say goodbye,

1704
02:16:52,337 --> 02:16:55,547
it suddenly reminds me of the day
I first came to Man-wol Inn.

1705
02:16:58,302 --> 02:16:59,642
Where do you think you're doing?

1706
02:17:09,480 --> 02:17:11,690
Are you stealing that knife

1707
02:17:12,149 --> 02:17:14,029
to kill everyone in that family?

1708
02:17:19,990 --> 02:17:21,370
My daughter...

1709
02:17:22,618 --> 02:17:24,998
The man who killed his own daughter

1710
02:17:26,246 --> 02:17:28,116
just welcomed a new child.

1711
02:17:28,207 --> 02:17:30,827
You won't be able to kill anyone
with that knife.

1712
02:17:34,588 --> 02:17:38,468
If you take this, you'll be able to kill
at least a few people.

1713
02:17:40,135 --> 02:17:42,795
After that, you'll get captured
and disappear into thin air

1714
02:17:43,263 --> 02:17:44,473
like you always wanted.

1715
02:17:48,852 --> 02:17:51,272
But the person
you actually want to kill is yourself

1716
02:17:51,355 --> 02:17:53,565
because you have failed to protect

1717
02:17:54,233 --> 02:17:55,483
your precious daughter.

1718
02:17:57,444 --> 02:17:59,664
If you stay here to go to the afterlife,

1719
02:17:59,738 --> 02:18:02,778
you'll get to live a new life.
But I know you don't want that.

1720
02:18:02,866 --> 02:18:05,236
You already hate yourself so much.

1721
02:18:05,744 --> 02:18:06,954
So, I'm sure

1722
02:18:07,829 --> 02:18:09,829
you'd want to throw it away
even if you have a chance.

1723
02:18:15,295 --> 02:18:19,295
In a way,
you may be the most suitable employee

1724
02:18:20,050 --> 02:18:22,550
for this guest house of the dead

1725
02:18:24,680 --> 02:18:27,640
since you are longing
for a perpetual death.

1726
02:18:28,559 --> 02:18:30,519
Do you long for the same thing?

1727
02:18:33,772 --> 02:18:35,652
The deity must have chained me here

1728
02:18:36,733 --> 02:18:39,153
because that's what they saw in me.

1729
02:18:43,407 --> 02:18:45,327
It started that day.

1730
02:18:46,368 --> 02:18:49,658
As I leaned on you while holding my grudge
and waited,

1731
02:18:50,247 --> 02:18:52,077
I wished

1732
02:18:53,041 --> 02:18:55,341
that you wouldn't change.

1733
02:19:02,551 --> 02:19:04,391
We were embracing our own hell then.

1734
02:19:04,469 --> 02:19:08,679
But now, we are leaving this world
in a decent way.

1735
02:19:09,349 --> 02:19:10,639
I'm glad for that.

1736
02:19:11,977 --> 02:19:15,147
As it's a happy occasion, let's not cry.

1737
02:19:16,064 --> 02:19:17,904
I will go with a smile.

1738
02:19:18,275 --> 02:19:19,275
Bye.

1739
02:19:27,909 --> 02:19:29,119
Ms. Choe.

1740
02:19:32,080 --> 02:19:33,330
Can I...

1741
02:19:35,250 --> 02:19:36,840
hug you?

1742
02:20:05,739 --> 02:20:07,779
I wasn't going to cry.

1743
02:20:09,785 --> 02:20:11,825
Why are you making me cry?

1744
02:20:36,728 --> 02:20:39,558
There were many times
when my heart broke for you.

1745
02:20:40,607 --> 02:20:42,147
I always wanted

1746
02:20:43,777 --> 02:20:45,857
to give you a hug like this.

1747
02:20:48,949 --> 02:20:50,369
Ms. Choe,

1748
02:20:51,618 --> 02:20:54,248
you have comforted me on many occasions.

1749
02:20:57,207 --> 02:20:58,377
Thank you.

1750
02:22:00,020 --> 02:22:01,270
How much time

1751
02:22:02,105 --> 02:22:03,855
do we have left?

1752
02:22:05,692 --> 02:22:06,902
Today,

1753
02:22:07,944 --> 02:22:09,744
around the time of a full moon,

1754
02:22:09,821 --> 02:22:13,161
all the energy at the hotel
will be collected.

1755
02:22:14,159 --> 02:22:16,409
Everything will disappear.

1756
02:22:16,703 --> 02:22:19,663
And Jang Man-wol must leave.

1757
02:22:20,832 --> 02:22:22,462
I've been wanting to ask you

1758
02:22:22,918 --> 02:22:23,958
why...

1759
02:22:25,337 --> 02:22:26,547
you chose me.

1760
02:22:27,547 --> 02:22:30,757
Why did you choose me?

1761
02:22:36,389 --> 02:22:38,809
I guess the flower that dreams of the moon

1762
02:22:39,059 --> 02:22:43,229
hasn't shown you the last dream yet.

1763
02:23:18,723 --> 02:23:20,313
I'm all alone now

1764
02:23:24,312 --> 02:23:25,652
just like how I started.

1765
02:24:19,492 --> 02:24:21,702
Ms. Jang, I wasn't dozing off.

1766
02:24:21,786 --> 02:24:24,456
I just closed my eyes for a second,
and my legs went weak.

1767
02:24:26,041 --> 02:24:27,921
That was a lie. I'm sorry.

1768
02:24:29,669 --> 02:24:32,009
We have a guest coming in.
You should go back to your office.

1769
02:24:34,216 --> 02:24:35,466
Welcome.

1770
02:24:35,842 --> 02:24:38,012
How long has it been
since you passed away?

1771
02:24:38,470 --> 02:24:41,560
Let me escort you to your room.
This way, please.

1772
02:25:15,715 --> 02:25:16,755
Ms. Jang,

1773
02:25:16,841 --> 02:25:19,931
the guest in Room 603 was supposed
to take the bus to the afterlife today

1774
02:25:20,011 --> 02:25:21,761
but wants to postpone it until tomorrow.

1775
02:25:22,847 --> 02:25:27,307
And these are steamed buns
requested by the guest in Room 1120.

1776
02:25:27,769 --> 02:25:30,609
The guest really misses
the steamed buns from childhood.

1777
02:25:30,939 --> 02:25:32,479
I'm going to bring these up.

1778
02:25:52,961 --> 02:25:57,091
Ms. Jang, I made a new cocktail.
Would you like to taste it?

1779
02:25:57,549 --> 02:26:01,049
Why don't you smell it at least?
Isn't the color pretty?

1780
02:26:01,428 --> 02:26:04,138
Come on, it does not look
like I washed rags in it.

1781
02:26:04,222 --> 02:26:07,182
And let's be honest.
Have you ever washed a rag?

1782
02:26:08,059 --> 02:26:09,229
Don't go. Stay there.

1783
02:26:09,311 --> 02:26:11,731
I'll go wash the rag and bring the water.
Let's compare them.

1784
02:26:11,938 --> 02:26:13,268
Stay right there!

1785
02:28:03,716 --> 02:28:06,336
You came to send off one last guest,

1786
02:28:08,388 --> 02:28:10,218
Chan-sung.

1787
02:28:27,407 --> 02:28:28,737
Chan-sung.

1788
02:28:30,869 --> 02:28:32,749
I feel so sleepy.

1789
02:28:34,456 --> 02:28:35,996
I feel like I'm falling asleep.

1790
02:28:38,334 --> 02:28:42,464
Maybe they want me to feel like
I'm dreaming when I leave.

1791
02:28:56,394 --> 02:28:58,354
I'll stay by your side
even if you fall asleep.

1792
02:29:38,394 --> 02:29:39,564
Now I've crossed

1793
02:29:41,272 --> 02:29:42,862
the long periods of time

1794
02:29:43,691 --> 02:29:44,821
and met you there,

1795
02:29:46,069 --> 02:29:48,319
embracing the flower

1796
02:29:49,906 --> 02:29:51,906
that is dreaming of the moon.

1797
02:29:58,498 --> 02:29:59,708
Your name means the "full moon".

1798
02:30:00,667 --> 02:30:01,787
It's pretty.

1799
02:30:02,877 --> 02:30:06,297
There's a place called
the Guest House of the Moon.

1800
02:30:36,911 --> 02:30:39,791
You're still here.

1801
02:30:39,872 --> 02:30:41,422
Because this place still exists.

1802
02:30:41,874 --> 02:30:43,044
How can I help you?

1803
02:30:43,293 --> 02:30:47,763
A long time ago, I lent a pair of scissors

1804
02:30:47,839 --> 02:30:51,219
to a bride who visited the hotel.
Do you remember?

1805
02:30:52,927 --> 02:30:56,387
You said you need more courage
to let go than to hold on.

1806
02:30:56,806 --> 02:30:58,306
You lent it to help her do that.

1807
02:30:58,850 --> 02:31:00,060
That's right.

1808
02:31:00,768 --> 02:31:05,148
The thing is,
I forgot to get it back from her.

1809
02:31:05,231 --> 02:31:06,571
I have it.

1810
02:31:07,650 --> 02:31:09,190
My gosh!

1811
02:31:09,944 --> 02:31:11,534
Thank goodness.

1812
02:31:15,700 --> 02:31:20,370
I should repay you for finding
this precious pair of scissors.

1813
02:31:20,455 --> 02:31:22,535
You deities never show up when I need you,

1814
02:31:22,624 --> 02:31:24,544
but you always return all favors.

1815
02:31:24,626 --> 02:31:26,036
What can I do for you?

1816
02:31:27,629 --> 02:31:30,969
Do you want me to cut the ties
between you and the one

1817
02:31:31,049 --> 02:31:32,549
who broke your heart?

1818
02:31:34,427 --> 02:31:36,427
Are we still connected?

1819
02:31:37,680 --> 02:31:39,470
Can you see it?

1820
02:31:39,557 --> 02:31:42,057
Are there still ties left to cut?

1821
02:31:42,143 --> 02:31:43,983
Well, that's...

1822
02:31:44,062 --> 02:31:48,112
I cannot answer that.

1823
02:31:51,611 --> 02:31:52,741
Forget it, then.

1824
02:31:55,823 --> 02:31:57,083
There's something I want.

1825
02:31:58,117 --> 02:31:59,657
I want to travel back in time.

1826
02:32:00,620 --> 02:32:03,040
-That's--
-I know you can do it.

1827
02:32:03,122 --> 02:32:04,462
You made me do it before.

1828
02:32:05,875 --> 02:32:07,585
That's true, but...

1829
02:32:07,669 --> 02:32:09,499
It's fine even if it's for a short moment.

1830
02:32:10,254 --> 02:32:11,304
Help me

1831
02:32:12,298 --> 02:32:14,008
see winter with her.

1832
02:33:22,493 --> 02:33:23,703
It's snowing.

1833
02:33:31,419 --> 02:33:33,249
Winter is really here.

1834
02:33:34,714 --> 02:33:37,554
Am I still dreaming?

1835
02:33:38,426 --> 02:33:42,426
This is the winter we're spending together
that you wanted.

1836
02:33:48,227 --> 02:33:49,977
Where did this come from?

1837
02:33:51,606 --> 02:33:54,186
Maybe from a time in our shared past,

1838
02:33:54,609 --> 02:33:56,439
or from a moment
we'll share in our future.

1839
02:33:57,612 --> 02:33:58,992
I'm not sure which one it is.

1840
02:34:00,072 --> 02:34:01,122
It's just winter

1841
02:34:02,700 --> 02:34:05,200
from one of the moments
we've shared or will spend together.

1842
02:34:08,080 --> 02:34:09,250
Chan-sung.

1843
02:34:10,917 --> 02:34:12,917
I saw you in my dream.

1844
02:34:24,514 --> 02:34:27,104
Man-wol. The moon.

1845
02:34:31,145 --> 02:34:32,475
Your name means the "full moon."

1846
02:34:34,774 --> 02:34:35,944
It's pretty.

1847
02:34:43,741 --> 02:34:47,871
We actually met again

1848
02:34:49,247 --> 02:34:51,367
after the long periods of time.

1849
02:34:56,879 --> 02:35:01,299
Then did this snow come from some winter
we spent together in our past?

1850
02:35:04,637 --> 02:35:07,387
I hope it came from our future
we'll spend together.

1851
02:35:12,603 --> 02:35:13,653
Really?

1852
02:35:18,067 --> 02:35:20,437
Now, the snow looks even prettier.

1853
02:36:31,682 --> 02:36:34,982
Are you going alone
without the Grim Reaper's guidance?

1854
02:36:36,354 --> 02:36:39,114
I've been the owner of this place
for all those years.

1855
02:36:40,608 --> 02:36:44,028
I will go on my own.

1856
02:36:46,906 --> 02:36:48,026
You're brave.

1857
02:36:54,538 --> 02:36:55,618
Chan-sung.

1858
02:36:59,502 --> 02:37:01,092
I've pondered...

1859
02:37:03,631 --> 02:37:05,841
countless times what I should tell you...

1860
02:37:08,260 --> 02:37:10,010
if this moment ever comes.

1861
02:37:14,433 --> 02:37:15,733
"I'm sorry."

1862
02:37:17,103 --> 02:37:18,483
"Thank you."

1863
02:37:20,773 --> 02:37:22,233
"Have a good life."

1864
02:37:27,279 --> 02:37:29,659
I came up with a lot of cool stuff
to tell you.

1865
02:37:31,534 --> 02:37:33,744
Now that it's time,
I don't know what to say.

1866
02:37:37,081 --> 02:37:38,081
I just...

1867
02:37:41,919 --> 02:37:44,459
I want to stay with you.

1868
02:37:48,592 --> 02:37:50,682
I just want to see you.

1869
02:37:54,974 --> 02:37:57,604
And I don't want to leave you behind here.

1870
02:38:06,485 --> 02:38:07,985
I knew I would be like this.

1871
02:38:09,071 --> 02:38:10,781
When I'm the weak one,

1872
02:38:10,990 --> 02:38:12,910
I pretended to be strong in front of you.

1873
02:38:13,826 --> 02:38:16,496
I even made it impossible for you

1874
02:38:18,372 --> 02:38:20,372
to stop me from leaving.

1875
02:38:29,467 --> 02:38:30,757
I'm sorry.

1876
02:38:48,110 --> 02:38:49,280
It was right here.

1877
02:38:49,945 --> 02:38:52,695
You told me not to feel lonely
when I see you off.

1878
02:38:54,784 --> 02:38:56,244
Were you pretending to be strong?

1879
02:38:56,660 --> 02:38:59,910
Back then, I didn't know
I'd like you this much.

1880
02:39:01,624 --> 02:39:02,674
I...

1881
02:39:04,710 --> 02:39:07,510
I also didn't know
I would fall in love once again.

1882
02:39:09,548 --> 02:39:10,838
Like a fool.

1883
02:39:25,523 --> 02:39:28,943
I've never thought

1884
02:39:29,902 --> 02:39:32,322
about the future before.

1885
02:39:34,365 --> 02:39:36,905
But the only thing I can tell you now

1886
02:39:38,369 --> 02:39:39,789
is this.

1887
02:39:48,254 --> 02:39:49,264
Let's

1888
02:39:50,631 --> 02:39:52,971
meet in our next lives again...

1889
02:39:55,719 --> 02:39:57,559
no matter what.

1890
02:40:00,057 --> 02:40:01,057
Okay?

1891
02:40:03,727 --> 02:40:04,727
Yes?

1892
02:40:17,867 --> 02:40:18,987
Chan-sung.

1893
02:40:20,911 --> 02:40:22,751
You looked into me,

1894
02:40:25,082 --> 02:40:26,292
took care of me,

1895
02:40:28,419 --> 02:40:29,799
and protected me.

1896
02:40:33,299 --> 02:40:34,719
And I thank you for that.

1897
02:40:40,014 --> 02:40:41,274
Goodbye.

1898
02:40:45,769 --> 02:40:47,559
Goodbye, Man-wol.

1899
02:43:00,779 --> 02:43:03,489
THE SAMDO RIVER

1900
02:44:07,679 --> 02:44:10,769
My dear moon disappeared
after swallowing up

1901
02:44:11,517 --> 02:44:12,847
all my nights and dreams.

1902
02:44:14,353 --> 02:44:15,603
Goodbye.

1903
02:44:24,530 --> 02:44:29,870
It's natural to feel sad and disappointed
when you let go of someone you love.

1904
02:44:31,703 --> 02:44:35,873
Just like a flower dreams of
blooming again while withering away,

1905
02:44:36,792 --> 02:44:40,712
you'll live, meet,

1906
02:44:41,088 --> 02:44:43,218
and love again.

1907
02:44:44,758 --> 02:44:46,178
I hope

1908
02:44:46,718 --> 02:44:49,258
that is the answer
you two, an arrogant, foolish,

1909
02:44:49,471 --> 02:44:51,521
and self-pitying

1910
02:44:51,890 --> 02:44:56,440
yet beautiful lovers, have chosen.

1911
02:46:51,552 --> 02:46:56,272
Merry Christmas!

1912
02:46:56,765 --> 02:46:57,805
It's cold.

1913
02:46:58,600 --> 02:46:59,770
Chan-sung.

1914
02:47:02,437 --> 02:47:04,937
Chan-sung. It's so freezing.

1915
02:47:05,023 --> 02:47:06,403
Hey, it's gotten really cold.

1916
02:47:06,483 --> 02:47:09,243
New York's just as cold as Seoul,
so don't forget your winter clothes.

1917
02:47:09,861 --> 02:47:12,491
Can you send me my things
once I settle down there?

1918
02:47:12,573 --> 02:47:15,623
Sure. Take what you can
and I'll bring the rest when I visit.

1919
02:47:15,701 --> 02:47:17,081
How about lunch tomorrow?

1920
02:47:18,495 --> 02:47:20,075
Actually, I have other plans.

1921
02:47:47,024 --> 02:47:49,284
-Have you been well, Yu-na?
-Yes.

1922
02:47:49,568 --> 02:47:52,148
How did you do on your exam?
Do you have a major in mind?

1923
02:47:52,237 --> 02:47:53,817
Hotel management.

1924
02:47:54,448 --> 02:47:56,368
I'm going to become a hotelier too.

1925
02:47:57,409 --> 02:47:58,869
You must've gotten a good score then.

1926
02:47:59,036 --> 02:48:01,076
I probably will next year.

1927
02:48:02,372 --> 02:48:06,422
Seeing ghosts and all that,
I couldn't focus on my studying this year.

1928
02:48:06,501 --> 02:48:10,051
Thanks to the medicine you gave me though,

1929
02:48:10,213 --> 02:48:12,223
I don't see them anymore.

1930
02:48:12,507 --> 02:48:15,337
It made me focus on studying.

1931
02:48:15,427 --> 02:48:16,347
I'm glad to hear that.

1932
02:48:16,428 --> 02:48:19,058
You also took the same medicine, right?

1933
02:48:20,474 --> 02:48:23,814
You don't see the ghosts now, right?

1934
02:48:43,121 --> 02:48:47,421
Do you think the tiger saw
what he wanted to see in the painting?

1935
02:48:49,586 --> 02:48:52,006
He saw the past like a dream,

1936
02:48:52,089 --> 02:48:54,089
a time where he could never go back.

1937
02:48:54,633 --> 02:48:56,513
He got pretty lucky.

1938
02:49:21,993 --> 02:49:23,873
My memory of a secretive world

1939
02:49:24,287 --> 02:49:26,417
others don't know about.

1940
02:49:29,918 --> 02:49:31,838
It is where you are.

1941
02:49:34,339 --> 02:49:35,589
And I...

1942
02:49:37,467 --> 02:49:39,847
still remember my promise to you.

1943
02:50:45,535 --> 02:50:49,955
EXISTENCE AND TIME

1944
02:51:39,464 --> 02:51:40,804
You're early.

1945
02:51:41,591 --> 02:51:43,091
I thought you'd be late.

1946
02:51:44,719 --> 02:51:46,429
I hurried over

1947
02:51:48,056 --> 02:51:49,466
so that you wouldn't wait.

1948
02:51:53,228 --> 02:51:54,438
Someday...

1949
02:51:56,606 --> 02:51:57,976
Someday...

1950
02:51:59,818 --> 02:52:03,948
If we meet again
in some life far down the road...

1951
02:52:05,198 --> 02:52:10,828
When that day ever comes,
I hope to always be with you.

1952
02:52:15,667 --> 02:52:20,207
We will dream together
looking each other in the eye,

1953
02:52:20,630 --> 02:52:23,170
embrace each other, and laugh together

1954
02:52:23,925 --> 02:52:25,585
as we

1955
02:52:26,303 --> 02:52:30,353
live happily together for a long time.

1956
02:54:11,449 --> 02:54:14,869
I'm about to make
an important announcement.

1957
02:54:14,953 --> 02:54:16,793
Where are the rest?

1958
02:54:17,038 --> 02:54:20,328
Is the sixth still living in Joseon?

1959
02:54:20,709 --> 02:54:22,169
Unbelievable.

1960
02:54:22,252 --> 02:54:26,382
Why is it that all 12 of us
are never able to congregate?

1961
02:54:26,464 --> 02:54:28,684
It's not like you're that busy.

1962
02:54:28,758 --> 02:54:32,718
You can talk to them later.

1963
02:54:33,221 --> 02:54:34,721
So what's the announcement?

1964
02:54:36,474 --> 02:54:39,854
I have chosen a surprising new owner

1965
02:54:39,936 --> 02:54:44,766
for the Guest House of the Moon.

1966
02:54:46,109 --> 02:54:50,199
Wandering souls
that have nowhere else to go

1967
02:54:51,281 --> 02:54:54,451
must have a place to stay
in order to tell their stories.

1968
02:54:55,285 --> 02:54:57,245
Then, what's the name of the new hotel?

1969
02:54:57,454 --> 02:55:01,424
Oh, that. Well, it's...

1970
02:55:03,626 --> 02:55:04,706
What was it again?

1971
02:55:06,963 --> 02:55:09,673
Wait. What's wrong with me?

1972
02:55:10,383 --> 02:55:11,893
Why can't I remember?

1973
02:56:19,953 --> 02:56:21,253
The moon has risen.

1974
02:56:23,039 --> 02:56:24,419
Let's open our doors.

1975
02:56:44,143 --> 02:56:46,353
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
